heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>2"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'Term used offence')
heading_40 = heading_8 + ">>An act or omission which renders the person doing the act or making the omission liable to punishment is called an offence."
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>3. Indictable offences, general provisions as to"
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'This section applies to offences in this Code and in any other written law.')
heading_43 = heading_41 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'An indictable offence is triable only on indictment, unless this Code or another written law expressly provides otherwise.')
heading_44 = heading_41 + ">>(3) A prosecution for an indictable offence, whether or not it may be tried summarily, may be commenced at any time, unless this Code or another written law expressly provides otherwise."
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>[(4) deleted]"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>(5) If a person is convicted by a court of summary jurisdiction of an indictable offence, the conviction is to be regarded as being a conviction of a simple offence only, unless the person is convicted of the offence by the Childrens Court under section 19B(4) of the"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'Childrens Court of Western Australia Act 1988 or another written law provides otherwise.')
heading_47 = heading_45 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'A person may be convicted and punished for an offence on indictment notwithstanding that the person might have been convicted of and punished for that offence summarily.')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_46, '[Section 3 inserted No. 4 of 2004 s. 28 amended No. 59 of 2004 s. 80 No. 70 of 2004 s. 36(1) No. 84 of 2004 s. 28.]')
heading_42 = heading_40 + ">>4."
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'Term used attempt to commit offence  When a person, intending to commit an offence, begins to put his intention into execution by doing an act that is more than merely preparatory to the commission of the offence but does not fulfil his intention to such an extent as to commit the offence, he is said to attempt to commit the offence.')
heading_41 = heading_8 + ">>content33"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'It is immaterial, except so far as regards punishment, whether the offender does all that is necessary on his part for completing the commission of the offence, or whether the complete fulfilment of his intention is prevented by circumstances independent of his will, or whether he desists of his own motion from the further prosecution of his intention.')
heading_42 = heading_8 + ">>content34"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'It is immaterial that by reason of circumstances not known to the offender, it is impossible in fact to commit the offence.')
heading_43 = heading_8 + ">>The same facts may constitute one offence and an attempt to commit another offence."
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>[Section 4 amended No. 106 of 1987 s. 5.]"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>5. Summary conviction penalty, meaning and effect of"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>(1) This section applies if "
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'a provision of this Code, or another written law, provides a summary conviction penalty for an indictable offence and')
heading_48 = heading_46 + ">>(b) a person (the accused"
CONTEXT(heading_48, ') is charged before a court of summary jurisdiction (the court ) with committing the indictable offence in circumstances where the summary conviction penalty applies to the offence (the charge ).')
heading_47 = heading_45 + ">>(2) Despite section 3(2), the court is to try the charge summarily unless "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'on an application made by the prosecutor or the accused before the accused pleads to the charge, the court')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'this Code or another written law expressly provides to the contrary.')
heading_48 = heading_45 + ">>(3) The court may decide the charge is to be tried on indictment if and only if it considers "
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>(a) that the circumstances in which the offence was allegedly committed are so serious that, if the accused were convicted of the offence, the court would not be able to adequately punish the accused or"
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>(ba) that the circumstances in which the offence was allegedly committed are such that, if the accused were convicted of the offence, the"
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'Sentencing Act 1995 Part 2 Division 2A would apply to the sentencing of the accused for that offence or')
heading_50 = heading_48 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'that the charge forms part of a course of conduct during which other offences were allegedly committed by the accused and the accused is to be tried on indictment for one or more of those other offences or')
heading_51 = heading_48 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'that a co-accused of the accused is to be tried on indictment or')
heading_52 = heading_48 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'that the charge forms part of a course of conduct during which other offences were allegedly committed by the accused and others and the accused or one of the others is to be tried on indictment for one or more of those other offences or')
heading_53 = heading_48 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'that the interests of justice require that the charge be dealt with on indictment.')
heading_49 = heading_45 + ">>(4) For the purposes of making a decision under subsection (3) the court "
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'may require the prosecutor to provide any information the court needs and may hear submissions from both the prosecutor and the accused and')
heading_51 = heading_49 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'may adjourn the proceedings.')
heading_50 = heading_45 + ">>(5) If under subsection (3) the court decides that the charge is to be tried on indictment the court shall "
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'give reasons for the decision and')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>(b) deal with the accused in accordance with section 41 of the"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'Criminal Procedure Act 2004 .')
heading_51 = heading_45 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'A decision cannot be made under subsection (3) after the accused has pleaded to the charge.')
heading_52 = heading_45 + ">>(7)"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'A decision made under subsection (3) is final and cannot be appealed.')
