heading_32 = heading_30 + ">>(2) When an arrangement is in force under this section "
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'the Registrar may perform, to the extent authorised by the arrangement (but subject to the conditions of the arrangement), the functions of the registering authority under the corresponding law and')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'the registering authority under the corresponding law may perform, to the extent authorised by the arrangement (but subject to the conditions of the arrangement), the functions of the Registrar under this Act.')
heading_33 = heading_30 + ">>(3) An arrangement under this section may "
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'establish a database in which information is recorded for the benefit of all the participants in the arrangement')
heading_35 = heading_33 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'provide for access to information contained in the database and')
heading_36 = heading_33 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'provide for payments by or to participants in the arrangement for services provided under the arrangement.')
heading_27 = heading_25 + ">>Part 3  Registration of births; Division 1  Notification of births; Division 1  Notification of births; Division 1  Notification of births; Division 1  Notification of births; Division 1  Notification of births; Division 1  Notification of births"
heading_28 = heading_27 + ">>12. Notification of births"
heading_29 = heading_28 + ">>(1) In this section ; responsible person, in relation to the birth of a child ; responsible person, in relation to the birth of a child ; responsible person, in relation to the birth of a child ; responsible person, in relation to the birth of a child ; responsible person, in relation to the birth of a child ; responsible person, in relation to the birth of a child "
heading_30 = heading_29 + ">>(a) if the child was born in a hospital or brought to a hospital within 24 hours after the childs birth, means "
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>(i) in the case of a public hospital as defined in the"
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>Health Services Act 2016 section 6  the chief executive of the health service provider for that hospital or  (ii) in the case of a private hospital as defined in the  Private Hospitals and Health Services Act 1927 section 2(1)  the chief executive officer or general manager of the hospital"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'or')
heading_31 = heading_29 + ">>(b) in any other case "
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>(i) means the doctor or midwife responsible for the professional care of the childs mother at the birth"
CONTEXT(heading_32, '(ii) if the child was still-born, means the doctor who examined the childs body after the birth or  (iii) if no doctor or midwife was in attendance at the childs birth, means any person in attendance at the birth.')
heading_30 = heading_28 + ">>(2) When a child is born in the State, the responsible person must give the Registrar notice of the birth "
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'within one month after the birth and')
heading_32 = heading_30 + ">>(b) in an approved form and manner."
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'Penalty $1 000.')
heading_31 = heading_28 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'A person does not commit an offence under subsection (2) if notice of the birth is given by another person.')
heading_26 = heading_22 + ">>[Section 12 amended No. 11 of 2016 s. 284.]; Division 2  Registration of births; Division 2  Registration of births; Division 2  Registration of births; Division 2  Registration of births; Division 2  Registration of births; Division 2  Registration of births"
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>13. Cases in which registration of birth is required or authorised"
heading_28 = heading_27 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'If a child is born in the State, the birth must be registered under this Act.')
heading_29 = heading_27 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'If a State court orders that a birth be registered in this State, the birth must be registered under this Act.')
heading_30 = heading_27 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_30, 'If a court of another State or of the Commonwealth makes a determination that a birth should be registered in this State, the birth may be registered under this Act if the Registrar considers that it is appropriate to do so.')
heading_31 = heading_27 + ">>(4) If a child is born "
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'in an aircraft during a flight to an airport in the State or')
heading_33 = heading_31 + ">>(b) on a vessel during a voyage to a port in the State,"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'the birth may be registered under this Act.')
heading_32 = heading_27 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'If a child is born outside the Commonwealth, but the child is to become (or in the case of a still-birth, was to become) a resident of the State, the birth may be registered under this Act.')
heading_33 = heading_27 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'The Registrar must not register a birth under subsection (4) or (5) if the birth is registered under a corresponding law.')
heading_28 = heading_26 + ">>14. How to have the birth of a child registered"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'A person has the birth of a child registered under this Act by lodging a statement (the birth registration statement) in an approved form.')
heading_29 = heading_26 + ">>15. Responsibility to have birth registered"
heading_30 = heading_29 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_30, 'The parents of a child are jointly responsible for having the childs birth registered under this Act (and must both sign the birth registration statement) but the Registrar may accept a birth registration statement from one of the parents if satisfied that it is impracticable for the other parent to join or be required to join in the application because of his or her death, disappearance, ill health or unavailability or the need to avoid unwarranted distress to obtain the signatures of both parents on the birth registration statement.')
heading_31 = heading_29 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'If a child is a foundling, the person with responsibility for the long-term care, welfare and development of the child is responsible for having the childs birth registered.')
heading_32 = heading_29 + ">>(3) The Registrar may accept a birth registration statement from a person who is not responsible for having the childs birth registered if satisfied that "
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'the person lodging the statement has knowledge of the relevant facts and')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'the childs parents are unable or unlikely to lodge a birth registration statement.')
heading_30 = heading_26 + ">>16. Obligation to have birth registered"
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>(1) A person who is responsible under section 15(1) or (2) for having a childs birth registered must ensure that a birth registration statement is lodged with the Registrar within 60 days after the date of the birth."
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'Penalty $1 000.')
heading_32 = heading_30 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'The Registrar must accept a birth registration statement even though it is lodged after the end of the 60 day period.')
heading_31 = heading_26 + ">>17. Registration of birth"
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'The Registrar is to register a birth by making an entry about the birth in the Register including such particulars as the Registrar considers appropriate to register the birth.')
heading_33 = heading_31 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'If the particulars available to the Registrar are incomplete the Registrar may register a birth on the basis of incomplete particulars.')
heading_32 = heading_26 + ">>18. Registration of parentage details"
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>(1) The Registrar is not to include information about the identity of a childs parents in the Register unless "
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'both parents of the child make a joint application for the inclusion of registrable information about that identity')
heading_35 = heading_33 + ">>(b) one parent of the child makes an application for the inclusion of registrable information about that identity and the other parent cannot join in the application because "
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>(i) he or she is dead"
CONTEXT(heading_36, '(ii) he or she cannot be found or   (iii) of some other reason')
heading_36 = heading_33 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'one parent of the child makes an application for the inclusion of registrable information about that identity and the Registrar is satisfied that the other parent does not dispute the correctness of that information')
heading_37 = heading_33 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'a State court orders the inclusion of registrable information about the identity in the Register or makes a finding that a particular person is a parent of a child')
heading_38 = heading_33 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'a court of another State or of the Commonwealth makes a determination that registrable information about the identity should be included in the Register or makes a finding that a particular person is a parent of a child and the Registrar considers that it is appropriate to include the information in the Register or')
heading_39 = heading_33 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'the Registrar is entitled under any law (including a law of another State or the Commonwealth) to make a presumption as to the identity of the childs parent.')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>(2) The Registrar may include information about the identity of a childs parent in the Register if "
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'the Registrar is not prohibited by subsection (1) from doing so')
heading_36 = heading_34 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'despite subsection (1), both parents are unable to give registrable information about the identity of a childs parent or parents for some reason or are unavailable and another person can provide information to the Registrars satisfaction as to the identity of the childs parent or parents or')
heading_37 = heading_34 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'despite subsection (1), one parent has provided the birth registration statement and the registrable information relates only to the identity of that parent.')
heading_27 = heading_22 + ">>[Section 18 amended No. 3 of 2002 s. 30.]"
heading_28 = heading_27 + ">>19. Addition of details after birth registration"
heading_29 = heading_28 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'Subject to section 18, a person may apply to the Registrar for the inclusion of additional registrable information about a persons birth registration in the Register.')
heading_30 = heading_28 + ">>(2) An application under subsection (1) "
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'must be made in writing')
heading_32 = heading_30 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'must include such information that may be required by the Registrar')
heading_33 = heading_30 + ">>(c) in relation to a child, may include a request that a different surname for the child be entered in the Register (the proposed surname"
CONTEXT(heading_33, ') and')
heading_34 = heading_30 + ">>(d) must, if the Registrar requires verification of the information contained in the application, be accompanied by a statutory declaration verifying the"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'information contained in the application and other evidence the Registrar may require.')
heading_31 = heading_28 + ">>(3) Subject to subsection (4), on an application under subsection (1) that includes a request that a different surname for a child be entered in the Register "
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'if the application is jointly made by both parents of the child, the Registrar may change the surname for the child entered in the Register to the proposed surname or')
heading_33 = heading_31 + ">>(b) if the application is not jointly made by both parents of the child, the Registrar may change the surname for the child entered in the Register to the proposed surname if "
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>(i) the childs other parent has died or"
CONTEXT(heading_34, '(ii) the childs other parent cannot be found but other children of the same parents are registered in the proposed surname.')
heading_32 = heading_28 + ">>(4) On an application under subsection (1) that includes a request that a different surname for a child be entered in the Register the Registrar may change the surname for the child entered in the Register to the proposed surname "
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'if the proposed surname is not a prohibited name and')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>(b) if the child is 12 years of age or more and "
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>(i) the child consents to the proposed surname or"
CONTEXT(heading_35, '(ii) the child is unable to understand the meaning and implications of the change of surname.')
heading_28 = heading_22 + ">>[Section 19 amended No. 3 of 2002 s. 31.]"
heading_29 = heading_28 + ">>Division 3  Court orders relating to registration of birth"
heading_30 = heading_29 + ">>20. Powers of State courts; A State court may, on application by an interested person or on its own initiative, order the Registrar to ; A State court may, on application by an interested person or on its own initiative, order the Registrar to ; A State court may, on application by an interested person or on its own initiative, order the Registrar to ; A State court may, on application by an interested person or on its own initiative, order the Registrar to ; A State court may, on application by an interested person or on its own initiative, order the Registrar to ; A State court may, on application by an interested person or on its own initiative, order the Registrar to "
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'register a birth or')
heading_32 = heading_30 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'include or correct registrable information about a birth or a childs parents in the Register.')
heading_31 = heading_29 + ">>21. Registration of birth etc. after court findings"
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>(1) If a State court finds that "
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'the birth of a person is not registered as required under this Act or a corresponding law')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'the registrable information contained in an entry about a birth in the Register under this Act or a corresponding law is incomplete or incorrect or')
heading_35 = heading_32 + ">>(c) information about the identity of a childs parents should be included in the Register under this Act or a corresponding law,"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'the State court may order the registration of the birth or order the inclusion or correction of registrable information in the Register or make a determination for the purposes of the corresponding law (as is applicable to the case).')
heading_33 = heading_31 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'The Registrar may register a birth or amend the Register in accordance with the determination of a court of another State or of the Commonwealth which has made a finding of a kind referred to in subsection (1) if the Registrar considers it is appropriate to do so.')
heading_30 = heading_28 + ">>Division 4  Childs name"
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>22. Name of child"
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'The birth registration statement for a child must state the name of the child.')
heading_33 = heading_31 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'Subsection (1) does not require a still-born child or a child who has a neonatal death to be named but nothing in this subsection prevents such a child from being named if the persons lodging the birth registration statement for the child so wish.')
heading_34 = heading_31 + ">>(3) The name is a matter of choice for the person or persons lodging the birth registration statement and nothing in this Act requires that "
