CONTEXT(heading_75, 'in relation to the commission, or alleged commission, of a minor cannabis related offence, was under 18 years of age when the offence was committed, or allegedly committed.')
heading_66 = heading_64 + ">>(2) In this Part the following abbreviations are used "
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'CIR for cannabis intervention requirement')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>CIS for cannabis intervention session."
CONTEXT(heading_68, '[Section 8B inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6 amended No. 56 of 2011 s. 7.]')
heading_65 = heading_63 + ">>8C. Operation of; Young Offenders Act 1994 unaffected; Young Offenders Act 1994 unaffected"
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>Nothing in this Part prevents a young person from being dealt with under the  Young Offenders Act 1994 Part 5 in respect of a minor cannabis related offence."
CONTEXT(heading_66, '[Section 8C inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_66 = heading_63 + ">>8D. Appointment of authorised persons"
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>The Commissioner may, in writing, appoint persons or classes of persons to be authorised persons for the purposes of section 8I or 8L, or for the purposes of both of those sections."
CONTEXT(heading_67, '[Section 8D inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_64 = heading_62 + ">>Division 2  Cannabis intervention requirements  [Heading inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]"
heading_65 = heading_64 + ">>8E. CIR may be given for minor cannabis related offence"
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'A police officer who has reason to believe that a person has committed a minor cannabis related offence may give a')
heading_67 = heading_65 + ">>(2) A police officer who believes "
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'that an alleged offender has committed more than one minor cannabis related offence and')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(b) that the alleged offences have arisen out of the same incident,"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'may give a single CIR in respect of all or some of the offences.')
heading_68 = heading_65 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'A CIR is to be given as soon as practicable, and in any event within 60 days, after an alleged offence is believed to have been committed.')
heading_69 = heading_65 + ">>(4) A CIR cannot be given in respect of an alleged offence (the; new offence ) if the alleged offender ; new offence ) if the alleged offender "
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'is an adult who, before the new offence was allegedly committed, had been convicted of a minor cannabis related offence or given a CIR and')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(b) was an adult when so convicted or given the CIR."
CONTEXT(heading_71, '[Section 8E inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_66 = heading_64 + ">>8F. Cannabis intervention requirement"
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>(1) A CIR is a notice in a form prescribed by the regulations "
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'containing a description of the alleged offence, or offences and')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(b) informing the alleged offender that "
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>(i) he or she may, in writing, elect to be prosecuted for the alleged offence, or offences, in a court, and informing the alleged offender how to make that election and"
CONTEXT(heading_70, '(ii) if he or she does not wish to be prosecuted for the alleged offence, or offences, in a court, the')
heading_70 = heading_67 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'informing the alleged offender as to how the alleged offender may arrange to complete a CIS.')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>(2) A person need only complete a single CIS for each CIR given to the person, even if the CIR is given in respect of more than one alleged offence."
CONTEXT(heading_68, '[Section 8F inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_67 = heading_64 + ">>8G. Young persons  special requirements about CIRs"
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>(1) A CIR cannot be given in respect of an alleged offence (the; new offence ) if the alleged offender ; new offence ) if the alleged offender "
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'is a young person who, before the new offence was allegedly committed, had been convicted of, or given a CIR in respect of, 2 or more minor cannabis related offences and')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'at least 2 of those offences arose out of separate incidents, or are alleged to have done so.')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(2) A police officer who gives a young person a CIR is to ensure that a responsible adult is given a copy of the CIR as soon as is reasonably practicable after the CIR is given to the young person, unless "
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'after reasonable enquiry, neither the whereabouts nor the address of a responsible adult can be ascertained or')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'in the circumstances it would be inappropriate to give a responsible adult a copy of the CIR.')
heading_70 = heading_67 + ">>(3) A young person who has been given 2 CIRs need only complete a single CIS in respect of the CIRs if both CIRs were given before the completion of the CIS."
CONTEXT(heading_70, '[Section 8G inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_68 = heading_64 + ">>8H. Referral of young persons at risk to juvenile justice teams"
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>(1) A police officer is to refer a young person at risk to a juvenile justice team where appropriate under the"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'Young Offenders Act 1994 in preference to charging the young person under this Act.')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>(2) In subsection (1) ; young person at risk means an alleged offender who is a young person ; young person at risk means an alleged offender who is a young person "
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'to whom the police officer would have given a CIR, but for section 8G(1) or')
heading_72 = heading_70 + ">>(b) who has been given a CIR and has not completed a CIS within 28 days or any further time allowed under section 8L, unless "
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>(i) the CIR has been withdrawn under section 8I or"
heading_74 = heading_73 + ">>(ii) the young person has elected to be prosecuted for the alleged offence in a court."
CONTEXT(heading_74, '[Section 8H inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_69 = heading_64 + ">>8I. Withdrawal of CIR"
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'An authorised person may withdraw a CIR by sending to the alleged offender a notice in a form prescribed by the regulations stating that the CIR has been withdrawn.')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'A CIR cannot be withdrawn if the alleged offender has completed a CIS in relation to the CIR.')
heading_72 = heading_69 + ">>(3) A CIR that is withdrawn is taken not to have been given to an alleged offender for the purposes of sections 8E(4) and 8G(1)."
CONTEXT(heading_72, '[Section 8I inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_65 = heading_62 + ">>Division 3  Cannabis intervention sessions  [Heading inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]"
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>8J. Cannabis intervention session"
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>(1) The purpose of a cannabis intervention session is to inform those who complete it about "
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'the adverse health and social consequences of cannabis use and')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'the laws relating to the use, possession and cultivation of cannabis and')
heading_70 = heading_67 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'effective strategies to address cannabis using behaviour.')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>(2) The CEO (Health) may, in writing, do any of the following "
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'having regard to subsection (1), approve the content of a cannabis intervention session')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'approve treatment providers to provide cannabis intervention sessions')
heading_71 = heading_68 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'give an approval under paragraph (b) subject to conditions to be obeyed by the treatment provider approved')
heading_72 = heading_68 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'cancel or amend an approval given under paragraph (a) or (b).')
heading_69 = heading_66 + ">>(3) For the purposes of this section, this Act is to be taken to be a relevant Act as referred to in the"
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>Health Legislation Administration Act 1984 section 9."
CONTEXT(heading_70, '[Section 8J inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_67 = heading_65 + ">>8K. Benefit of completing CIS"
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'If the alleged offender has completed a CIS in respect of a CIR within 28 days or such further time as is allowed under section 8L, the bringing of proceedings and the imposition of penalties are prevented to the same extent that they would be')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(2) Completion of a CIS is not to be regarded as an admission for the purposes of any proceedings, whether civil or criminal."
CONTEXT(heading_69, '[Section 8K inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_68 = heading_65 + ">>8L. Extension of time to complete CIS"
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'An authorised person may, in a particular case, extend the period of 28 days within which the alleged offender may complete a CIS.')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>(2) The extension may be allowed whether or not the period of 28 days has elapsed."
CONTEXT(heading_70, '[Section 8L inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_69 = heading_65 + ">>8M. Certificate of completion of CIS"
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>(1) A treatment provider approved to provide a CIS under section 8J(2)(b) is to "
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'give to a person who has completed a CIS a certificate of completion and')
heading_72 = heading_70 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'send a copy of the certificate to the Commissioner.')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(2) A certificate of completion is to be in a form prescribed by the regulations and is to set out "
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'the name and address of the person who has completed the CIS and')
heading_73 = heading_71 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'the date of completion and')
heading_74 = heading_71 + ">>(c) the details of the CIR in respect of which the CIS was completed."
CONTEXT(heading_74, '[Section 8M inserted No. 45 of 2010 s. 6.]')
heading_63 = heading_59 + ">>Part IIIB  Psychoactive substances  [Heading inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]"
heading_64 = heading_63 + ">>8N. Terms used"
heading_65 = heading_64 + ">>(1) In this Part ; Agvet Code of Western Australia has the meaning given in the  Agricultural and Veterinary Chemicals (Western Australia) Act 1995; Agvet Code of Western Australia has the meaning given in the  Agricultural and Veterinary Chemicals (Western Australia) Act 1995"
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'consume has the meaning given in subsection (2)')
heading_67 = heading_65 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'manufacture, in relation to a psychoactive substance, means to make, prepare, produce, process (including by extracting or refining), package or label the psychoactive substance')
heading_68 = heading_65 + ">>psychoactive effect, in relation to a person who consumes a substance, means "
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'the effect of stimulating or depressing the central nervous system of the person, resulting in hallucinations or a significant disturbance in, or significant change to, motor function, thinking, behaviour, perception, awareness or mood or')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'the effect of causing a state of dependence, including physical or psychological addiction')
heading_69 = heading_65 + ">>content4"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'psychoactive substance means any substance that, when consumed by a person, has the capacity to induce a psychoactive effect on the person')
heading_70 = heading_65 + ">>content5"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'substance includes a natural organism.')
heading_66 = heading_64 + ">>(2) For this Part, a person consumes a substance if "
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'the substance is administered to the person, whether the person self-administers it or it is administered by another person or')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>(b) the person smokes, inhales or ingests the substance."
CONTEXT(heading_68, '[Section 8N inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]')
heading_65 = heading_63 + ">>8O. Application of this Part to particular substances"
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>(1) This Part does not apply to any of the following "
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>(a) either "
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>(i) a medicine or a Schedule 9 poison as those terms are defined in the"
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'Medicines and Poisons Act 2014 section 3 or  (ii) if the')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>Medicines and Poisons Act 2014 section 137 has not commenced  a medicine as defined in the"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'Poisons Act 1964 section 5(1) or included in Schedule 9 under the  Poisons Act 1964  1')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>(b) a therapeutic good included in the Register as defined in the"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'Therapeutic Goods Act 1989  (Commonwealth) section 3(1) or that is exempted from the operation of Part 3-2 of that Act by regulations made under section 18 of that Act')
heading_69 = heading_66 + ">>(c) a tobacco product as defined in the"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'Tobacco Products Control Act 2006  Glossary')
heading_70 = heading_66 + ">>(d) a substance referred to in paragraph (a) or (b) of the definition of liquor in the"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'Liquor Control Act 1988 section 3(1)')
heading_71 = heading_66 + ">>(e) a food as defined in the"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'Food Act 2008 section 8')
heading_72 = heading_66 + ">>(f) a substance that is a chemical product as defined in the Agvet Code of Western Australia if "
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>(i) the active constituents for the chemical product are approved under the Agvet Code of Western Australia Part 2 or"
CONTEXT(heading_73, '(ii) the chemical product is registered under the Agvet Code of Western Australia Part 2')
heading_73 = heading_66 + ">>g"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'a plant or fungus, or an extract from a plant or fungus')
heading_74 = heading_66 + ">>h"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'a substance of a class prescribed by the regulations.')
heading_67 = heading_65 + ">>(2) Despite subsection (1), this Part applies to a substance listed in subsection (1) if the substance contains, or has added to it, a substance that is not listed in subsection (1)."
CONTEXT(heading_67, '[Section 8O inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]')
heading_66 = heading_63 + ">>8P. Effect of representing substance as psychoactive substance"
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'For the purposes of this Part, a substance that is represented in any way as being a psychoactive substance is to be taken to be a psychoactive substance.')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>(2) For the purposes of this Part, a substance that is represented in any way as being a specified psychoactive substance is to be taken to be the specified psychoactive substance."
CONTEXT(heading_68, '[Section 8P inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]')
heading_67 = heading_63 + ">>8Q. Manufacture, sale or supply of psychoactive substances"
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>(1) A person commits a simple offence if the person manufactures a psychoactive substance."
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'Penalty a fine of $48 000 or imprisonment for 4 years or both.')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(2) A person commits a simple offence if the person sells or supplies a psychoactive substance."
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'Penalty a fine of $48 000 or imprisonment for 4 years or both.')
heading_70 = heading_67 + ">>(3) For the purpose of deciding whether or not a person has committed an offence under subsection (1) or (2) in relation to a substance, it is irrelevant that usage instructions concerning the substance given in any manner or form indicate that the substance is not a psychoactive substance or that it is not intended for human consumption."
CONTEXT(heading_70, '[Section 8Q inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]')
heading_68 = heading_63 + ">>8R. Promoting psychoactive substances"
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>(1) A person commits a simple offence if the person "
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'promotes a substance as having a psychoactive effect on a person who consumes the substance or')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(b) provides information in any form on how or where a psychoactive substance may be acquired."
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'Penalty a fine of $24 000 or imprisonment for 2 years or both.')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>(2) For the purposes of subsection (1)(a), a person promotes a substance if the person takes any action that is intended or apparently intended to publicise or promote the substance, whether visual or auditory means are employed and whether the substance is directly depicted or referred to or symbolism of some kind is employed, including action of a kind prescribed by the regulations."
CONTEXT(heading_70, '[Section 8R inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]')
heading_69 = heading_63 + ">>8S. Powers of police officers for purposes of this Part"
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>(1) A police officer may, for the purposes of this Part, with such assistance as the police officer considers necessary "
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>(a) enter the premises (other than residential premises) of a person who is suspected on reasonable grounds of "
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>(i) manufacturing, selling or supplying a psychoactive substance or"
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>(ii) promoting a substance as having a psychoactive effect on a person who consumes the substance or  (iii) providing information on how or where a psychoactive substance may be acquired or  (iv) having done any of the things mentioned in subparagraph (i) to (iii)"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'and')
heading_72 = heading_70 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'demand the production of, and inspect, any books, papers or documents relating to any of the things mentioned in paragraph (a)(i) to (iii) and')
heading_73 = heading_70 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'inspect any substances.')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'Section 25 applies as if the reference in subsection (1) of that section to a police officer exercising the powers conferred by section 22 or 23 included a reference to a police officer exercising the powers in subsection (1).')
heading_72 = heading_69 + ">>(3) Section 29 applies as if "
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'references in paragraphs (a) and (b) of that section to a police officer acting in the exercise of the powers conferred on the police officer by or under Part V or a person assisting a police officer so acting included a reference to a police officer acting in the exercise of the powers in subsection (1) or a person assisting a police officer so acting and')
heading_74 = heading_72 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'the reference in paragraph (b) of that section to books, papers, documents, information or stocks referred to in section 22 included a reference to books, papers, documents or substances referred to in subsection (1).')
heading_73 = heading_69 + ">>(4) The powers in subsection (1) are in addition to, and not in derogation of, the powers conferred on police officers by Part V."
CONTEXT(heading_73, '[Section 8S inserted No. 29 of 2015 s. 4.]')
heading_70 = heading_63 + ">>8T. Powers to seize and dispose of thing suspected of being psychoactive substance"
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>(1) In this section and section 8U "
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'destruction notice means a notice that complies with subsections (4) and (5).')
heading_72 = heading_70 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'If there are reasonable grounds to suspect that any thing found or received during the exercise of the powers conferred by')
heading_73 = heading_70 + ">>(3) A police officer must give to a person from whom a thing is seized under subsection (2) a destruction notice if "
heading_74 = heading_73 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'the police officer is satisfied that no person will be tried with the commission of an offence in relation to the thing or')
heading_75 = heading_73 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'a person is tried with the commission of an offence in relation to the thing and the person is not convicted of that offence.')
heading_74 = heading_70 + ">>(4) A destruction notice must "
heading_75 = heading_74 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'be in writing in the prescribed form and')
heading_76 = heading_74 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_76, 'identify the thing to which it relates and')
heading_77 = heading_74 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'advise that the thing will be destroyed on or after a day specified in the notice unless, before that day, an application is made under section 8U(1) to have a sample of the thing analysed.')
heading_75 = heading_70 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'The day referred to in subsection (4)(c) cannot be a day that is sooner than 21 days after the day the notice is given.')
