heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>(1) Subject to this section and sections 6 and 7, this Act applies to any residential tenancy agreement entered into, renewed, extended, assigned or otherwise transferred after the commencement of this Act.  (1A) This Act does not apply to a residential tenancy agreement that is a strata lease, within the meaning of the"
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>Strata Titles Act 1985 ."
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'Note for this subsection  This subsection does not affect the application of this Act to a residential tenancy agreement that is a sublease of a strata lease.')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>(2) This Act does not apply to any residential tenancy agreement in any of the following circumstances "
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'where the tenant is a party to an agreement for the sale and purchase of the premises, unless the period of the tenancy is one month or longer')
heading_36 = heading_34 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'where the agreement arises under a mortgage in respect of the premises')
heading_37 = heading_34 + ">>(c) where the agreement arises under a scheme under which "
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>(i) a group of adjacent premises is owned by a company and"
CONTEXT(heading_38, '(ii) the premises comprising the group are let by the company to persons who jointly have a controlling interest in the company')
heading_38 = heading_34 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'where the tenant is a boarder or lodger')
heading_39 = heading_34 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'where the agreement is bona fide entered into for the purpose of conferring on a person a right to occupy premises for a holiday')
heading_40 = heading_34 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'where the agreement is entered into as lessor, whether generally or in prescribed circumstances, by any prescribed person or agency being a person or agency that is acting on behalf of the Crown')
heading_41 = heading_34 + ">>g"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'where the agreement is a prescribed agreement, or is an agreement of a prescribed class.')
heading_35 = heading_32 + ">>(3) This Act does not apply to or in relation to any of the following "
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'any part of a hotel or motel')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>(b) accommodation for students provided "
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>(i) by an educational institution or"
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_39, '(ii) by an entity, other than the educational institution, if the accommodation is provided other than for the purpose of making a profit,  unless the accommodation is prescribed, or is of a class prescribed, for the purposes of this paragraph')
heading_40 = heading_38 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_40, '(ca) any part of a hospital or nursing home')
heading_38 = heading_35 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'any premises used for the purposes of a club')
heading_39 = heading_35 + ">>(d) any premises used to provide residential care to approved care recipients by an approved provider as defined in the"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'Aged Care Act 1997  (Commonwealth)')
heading_40 = heading_35 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'any prescribed premises or premises of a prescribed class.')
heading_36 = heading_32 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'For the purposes of subsection (2)(e), an agreement conferring a right to occupy premises for a fixed term of 3 months or longer shall be deemed, in the absence of proof to the contrary, not to have been entered into bona fide for the purpose of conferring a right to occupy the premises for a holiday.')
heading_37 = heading_32 + ">>(5) Subject to subsection (6), this Act applies to a site at a caravan park, within the meaning of the"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'Caravan Parks and Camping Grounds Act 1995 (whether or not a caravan, within the meaning of that Act, is situated on that site) as if the site was residential premises for the purposes of this Act.')
heading_38 = heading_32 + ">>(6) This Act does not apply to a site at a residential park, within the meaning of the"
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>Residential Parks (Long-stay Tenants) Act 2006, other than in relation to a residential tenancy agreement "
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'under which a person has a right to occupy such a site and')
heading_41 = heading_39 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'that is an existing fixed term long-stay agreement made in writing, to which the')
heading_40 = heading_38 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'Residential Parks (Long-stay Tenants) Act 2006 does not apply in accordance with section 6(4) of that Act.')
heading_39 = heading_32 + ">>(7) Subsection (6) has effect despite section 8(1) of the"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'Residential Parks (Long-stay Tenants) Act 2006 .')
heading_31 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 5 amended No. 34 of 1995 s. 33 No. 32 of 2006 s. 98 No. 60 of 2011 s. 6 No. 30 of 2018 s. 182.]"
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>6. Modification of application of Act by regulation; The Governor may by regulation provide that a provision of this Act shall not apply to or in relation to, or shall apply in a modified manner to, the following, or any combination of the following "
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'any residential tenancy agreement or class of residential tenancy agreements or')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'any premises or class of premises or')
heading_35 = heading_32 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'any prescribed person or agency being a person or agency that is acting on behalf of the Crown.')
heading_33 = heading_31 + ">>7. Transitional provisions relating to commencement of this Act"
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>(1) Where "
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'a residential tenancy agreement was entered into before the commencement of this Act and continues after such commencement and')
heading_36 = heading_34 + ">>(b) the tenancy under the agreement is a periodic tenancy,"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'this Act shall, subject to any other provision of this Act, apply to the agreement on and from the first day after such commencement on which rent is payable under the agreement.')
heading_35 = heading_33 + ">>(2) Where this Act applies to a residential tenancy agreement by virtue of subsection (1) "
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'any proceedings commenced in relation to the agreement before that application may be continued and completed as if this Act had not come into operation and')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'any notice to quit given in relation to the agreement before that application shall have effect and may be enforced as if this Act had not come into operation and')
heading_38 = heading_35 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'any process commenced before that application, being a process whereby the rent may be increased under the agreement, may be continued and completed and shall have effect to increase the rent as if this Act had not come into operation, but subject to any order under section 32 and')
heading_39 = heading_35 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'proceedings may be brought subject to and in accordance with this Act in respect of any cause of action that arose before that application, not being a cause of action subject to proceedings at the time of that application and')
heading_40 = heading_35 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'no civil or criminal liability shall be incurred by virtue of that application in respect of any act or omission before that application.')
heading_36 = heading_33 + ">>(3) Where "
heading_37 = heading_36 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'this Act becomes applicable to a residential tenancy agreement by reason of a renewal, extension, assignment or transfer referred to in section 5(1) and')
heading_38 = heading_36 + ">>(b) at the time of such application a security bond in respect of the agreement has been paid to the lessor or a person acting on the lessors behalf,"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'the following provisions apply ')
heading_39 = heading_36 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'the lessor shall cause the person who is holding the security bond to pay the amount of the security bond allowed by section 29(1), or such lesser amount as is held, to the bond administrator')
heading_40 = heading_36 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'each payment referred to in paragraph (c) shall be made not later than 21 days after this Act becomes applicable to the residential tenancy agreement')
heading_41 = heading_36 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'any amount paid to the bond administrator must be credited to the Rental Accommodation Account and is to be taken, for the purposes of this Act, to have been paid under section 29(4)(b).')
heading_37 = heading_33 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'Nothing in section 29(4) applies to a periodic tenancy to which this Act becomes applicable by virtue of subsection (1).')
heading_32 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 7 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 56 No. 77 of 2006 Sch. 1 cl. 149(5) No. 60 of 2011 s. 7 and 89.]; Part II  Administration"
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>7A. Commissioner"
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>(1) The Minister is required, by notice published in the"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'Gazette, to designate a person who is an executive officer of the Department as the Commissioner for the purposes of this Act.')
heading_35 = heading_33 + ">>(2) The Commissioner may be referred to by a title specified by the Minister by notice published in the"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'Gazette .')
heading_36 = heading_33 + ">>(3) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'executive officer has the meaning given by section 3(1) of the  Public Sector Management Act 1994 .')
heading_33 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 7A inserted No. 28 of 2006 s. 134.]"
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>8. Functions of Commissioner"
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>(1) The Commissioner has the following functions for the purposes of this Act "
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'the investigation of and conduct of research into matters relating to the interests of parties to residential tenancy agreements generally or any particular party or parties')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'the publication of reports and guidelines and the dissemination of information on matters relating to the interests of parties to residential tenancy agreements')
heading_38 = heading_35 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'the giving of advice to persons on the provisions of this Act or any other law relating to or affecting the interests of parties to residential tenancy agreements')
heading_39 = heading_35 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'the investigation, upon the complaint of a party to a residential tenancy agreement or otherwise, of an offence against this Act or of an infringement of a partys rights arising out of any residential tenancy')
heading_40 = heading_35 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'the making of reports to the Minister on matters referred to the Commissioner by the Minister and matters of importance investigated by the Commissioner, whether referred to the Commissioner by the Minister or not')
heading_41 = heading_35 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'another function conferred or imposed on the Commissioner by this Act')
heading_42 = heading_35 + ">>g"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'another function prescribed for the Commissioner.')
heading_34 = heading_27 + ">>[(2) deleted]  [Section 8 amended No. 28 of 2006 s. 135 No. 11 of 2024 s. 6.]"
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>9. Commissioner may institute or defend proceedings for party   [(1A) deleted]"
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'The Commissioner may, upon being satisfied that there is a cause of action and that it is in the public interest, on behalf of any party to a residential tenancy agreement, institute legal proceedings against any other person or defend any proceedings brought against the party or assume the conduct of proceedings already commenced by or against the party, with a view to enforcing or protecting the rights of the party in relation to any infringement or suspected infringement by that other person of those rights or of any of the provisions of this Act or other law relating to the interests of such parties.')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'The Commissioner may, if the Commissioner considers it appropriate, on behalf of any tenant, institute proceedings under section 32 or assume the conduct of proceedings already commenced under that section by the tenant.')
heading_38 = heading_35 + ">>(3) The Commissioner shall not institute, defend or assume the conduct of, any proceedings under subsection (1) or (2) on behalf of a party "
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>(a) without first "
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>(i) obtaining the written consent of the party which once given shall be irrevocable except with the consent of the Commissioner and"
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>(ii) obtaining the written consent of the Minister which may be given subject to such conditions as the Minister thinks fit"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'and')
heading_40 = heading_38 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'in relation to a residential tenancy agreement that has terminated unless a complaint is made to the Commissioner by a person who was a party to that agreement within 3 months after termination of the residential tenancy agreement.')
heading_39 = heading_35 + ">>(4) In relation to any proceedings referred to in subsection (1) or (2) the following provisions shall apply "
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'the Commissioner shall, on behalf of the party to the residential tenancy agreement, have in all respects the same rights in, and control over, the proceedings, including the right to settle any action or part of any action, as the party would have had in the conduct of those proceedings and')
heading_41 = heading_39 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'the Commissioner may, without consulting or seeking the consent of the party, conduct the proceedings in such manner as the Commissioner thinks appropriate and proper and')
heading_42 = heading_39 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'in the case of proceedings already commenced by or against the party, the court hearing the proceedings shall, on the application of the Commissioner, order that the Commissioner be substituted for the party as a party to the proceedings, and may make such other orders or give')
heading_43 = heading_39 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'any moneys (excluding costs) recovered by the Commissioner shall belong and be paid to the party without deduction and any amount awarded against the party shall be paid by and recoverable from the party, but in all cases the costs of the proceedings shall be borne by or paid to and retained by the Commissioner as the case may require and')
heading_44 = heading_39 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'if any party to the proceedings alleges another cause of action, or if the party on whose behalf the proceedings are being defended has another cause of action, the court hearing the proceedings shall, on the application of the Commissioner, order that the proceedings for the other cause of action be heard separately and that the party be a party to those proceedings in the partys own right and may make such other orders or give such other directions in that behalf as the court thinks fit.')
heading_40 = heading_35 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'In any proceedings referred to in subsection (1), a document purporting to be signed by the Commissioner stating in respect of the proceedings that the Commissioner is satisfied that there is a cause of action and that it is in the public interest to institute, defend or assume the conduct of the proceedings, as the case may be, on behalf of the party to the residential tenancy agreement shall, in the absence of proof to the contrary, be accepted as proof that the Commissioner instituted, defended or assumed the conduct of the proceedings, as the case may be, in accordance with that subsection.')
heading_41 = heading_35 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'In any proceedings referred to in subsection (2), a document purporting to be signed by the Commissioner stating in respect of the proceedings that the Commissioner considers it appropriate to institute or assume the conduct of the proceedings, as the case may be, on behalf of the tenant shall, in the absence of proof to the contrary, be accepted as proof that the Commissioner instituted or assumed the conduct of the')
heading_42 = heading_35 + ">>(7) In any proceedings referred to in subsection (1) or (2) "
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'a document purporting to be the consent of the party to the residential tenancy agreement to the Commissioner instituting, defending or assuming the conduct of the proceedings, as the case may be or')
heading_44 = heading_42 + ">>(b) a document purporting to be the Ministers consent to the Commissioner instituting, defending or assuming the conduct of the proceedings, as the case may be,"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'shall, in the absence of proof to the contrary, be accepted as proof of the matters referred to in the document.')
heading_43 = heading_35 + ">>(8)"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'Any money which the Commissioner becomes liable to pay by virtue of this section shall be charged to the Consolidated Account and this subsection, without any further appropriation, shall be sufficient authority for any such payment.')
heading_44 = heading_35 + ">>(9)"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'Any costs received by the Commissioner under subsection (4)(d) shall be credited to the Consolidated Account.')
heading_35 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 9 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 6 of 1993 s. 11 No. 59 of 1995 s. 56 No. 59 of 2004 s. 121 No. 77 of 2006 s. 4 No. 60 of 2011 s. 8 No. 11 of 2024 s. 7.]"
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>10. Delegation"
heading_37 = heading_36 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'The Commissioner may delegate any power or duty of the Commissioner under another provision of this Act to another employee of the Department.')
heading_38 = heading_36 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'The bond administrator may delegate any power or duty of the bond administrator under another provision of this Act to another employee of the Department.')
heading_39 = heading_36 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'The delegation must be in writing signed by the Commissioner or bond administrator, as the case requires.')
heading_40 = heading_36 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'A person to whom a power or duty has been delegated under this section cannot delegate that power or duty.')
heading_41 = heading_36 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'A person exercising a power or performing a duty that has been delegated to the person under this section is taken to do so in accordance with the terms of the delegation unless the contrary is shown.')
heading_42 = heading_36 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'Nothing in this section limits the ability of the Commissioner or the bond administrator to perform a power or duty through an officer or agent.')
heading_36 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 10 inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 8.]"
heading_37 = heading_36 + ">>11. Protection from liability"
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'A person is not liable for anything that the person has done, in good faith, in the performance or purported performance of a function under this Act.')
heading_39 = heading_37 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'The State is also relieved of any liability that it might have had for another person having done anything described in subsection (1).')
heading_40 = heading_37 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'The protection given by this section applies even though the thing done as described in subsection (1) may have been capable of being done whether or not this Act had been enacted.')
heading_41 = heading_37 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'In this section, a reference to doing a thing includes a reference to omitting to do the thing.')
heading_37 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11 inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 8.]   11AA. Disclosure of bond information"
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>(1) In this section "
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>bond information means information held by, or on behalf of, the bond administrator relating to, or arising from, the payment to the bond administrator of "
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'the security bond for a residential tenancy agreement or')
heading_41 = heading_39 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'a tenant compensation bond payable under a tenant compensation order')
heading_40 = heading_38 + ">>relevant entity means each of the following "
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'the chief executive officer of the Department')
heading_42 = heading_40 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'the Commissioner')
heading_43 = heading_40 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'the Housing Authority')
heading_44 = heading_40 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'the Magistrates Court.')
heading_39 = heading_37 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'The bond administrator may disclose bond information, including personal information, to a relevant entity to the extent the information is required by the relevant entity in the course of the entitys duties or functions.')
heading_40 = heading_37 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'The bond administrator may enter into an arrangement with a relevant entity for the purposes of facilitating the disclosure of information under subsection (2).')
heading_38 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11AA inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 9.]"
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>11A. Information officially obtained to be confidential"
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>(1) A person who misuses information obtained by reason of any function that person has, or at any time had, in the administration of this Act commits an offence."
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $20 000.')
heading_41 = heading_39 + ">>(2) A person misuses information if it is, directly or indirectly, recorded, used, or disclosed to another person, other than "
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'in the course of duty or')
heading_43 = heading_41 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'as required or allowed under this Act or another written law or')
heading_44 = heading_41 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'for the purposes of the investigation of any suspected offence or the conduct of proceedings against any person for an offence or')
heading_45 = heading_41 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'in a manner that could not reasonably be expected to lead to the identification of any person to whom the information refers or')
heading_46 = heading_41 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'with the consent of the person to whom the information relates, or each of them if there is more than one.')
heading_42 = heading_39 + ">>(3) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'information means information concerning the affairs of a person.')
heading_39 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11A inserted No. 28 of 2006 s. 136 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 10 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25 No. 11 of 2024 s. 10.]"
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>11B. Powers of investigation"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'The Fair Trading Act 2010 section 61 and Part 6 of that Act apply to this Act.')
heading_40 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11B inserted No. 58 of 2010 s. 189.]; Part III  Determination of disputes  Division 1 ; Provisions relating to applications made or referred to Commissioner [Heading inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>11C. Application of Division; This Division applies in relation to "
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>(a) any of the following applications made or referred to the Commissioner "
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>(i) a lessors application under section 50E, 50F, 50S or 50T"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_44, '(ii) a tenants application under section 50G, 50H, 50U or 50V')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>(iii) a security bond release application referred by the bond administrator under section 81I"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'or')
heading_43 = heading_41 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'an application made to the Commissioner in relation to a disputed tenancy matter.')
heading_41 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11C inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>11D. Parties to application; In this Division, a party to an application made in relation to a residential tenancy agreement is "
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'each party to the agreement who made the application and')
heading_44 = heading_42 + ">>(b) each other person who is "
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>(i) for a security bond release application  given notice of the application by the bond administrator under section 81F(2) or"
CONTEXT(heading_45, '(ii) otherwise  known to the Commissioner as a lessor, tenant or co-tenant under the residential tenancy agreement.')
heading_42 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11D inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>11E. Disputed tenancy matters"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>(1) A regulation may prescribe a matter (a disputed tenancy matter"
CONTEXT(heading_44, ') relating to the rights and obligations of the parties to a residential tenancy agreement as a matter about which the Commissioner may make decisions if the parties to a residential tenancy agreement are in dispute about the matter.')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'A party to a residential tenancy agreement may apply to the Commissioner to make an order stated in the application in relation to a disputed tenancy matter.')
heading_43 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11E inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>11F. Notice of application and invitation to make submissions"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>(1) This section applies to an application other than a security bond release application."
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'Note for this subsection  See section 81Q in relation to the Commissioner giving notice of receipt of a security bond release application and inviting submissions.')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'The Commissioner must give written notice of the receipt of the application to each party to the application.')
heading_47 = heading_44 + ">>(3) The notice must state that "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'the party may make a submission to the Commissioner about the application and')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'if the party makes a submission to the Commissioner by the day stated in the notice, the Commissioner will consider the partys submission in deciding the application.')
heading_44 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11F inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>11G. Commissioner may require further information"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'The Commissioner may give a party to an application a notice requiring the party to give the Commissioner the information stated in the notice.')
heading_47 = heading_45 + ">>(2) The Commissioner may, in the notice, require the person to do either or both of the following by the day stated in the notice "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'provide evidence to support a claim made by the person or')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'verify the information or evidence the person gives to the Commissioner by statutory declaration or in another way.')
heading_48 = heading_45 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'If the party does not comply with the requirement by the stated day, the Commissioner may decide the application without the persons information and the notice given to the party under subsection (2) must state that fact.')
heading_49 = heading_45 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'The Commissioner may, in writing, extend the period stated in the notice.')
heading_45 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11G inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>11H. False or misleading information"
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>(1) A person must not give the Commissioner information in relation to the application that the person knows, or ought reasonably to know, is false or misleading in a material particular."
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $10 000.')
heading_48 = heading_46 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'For subsection (1), it is immaterial whether the information was given in response to a requirement under section 11G or for another reason.')
heading_46 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11H inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>11I. Deciding application"
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'The Commissioner must decide an application on the information available to the Commissioner.')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'Subsection (1) does not limit another provision of this Act that provides for matters the Commissioner must consider or be satisfied of in deciding the application.')
heading_50 = heading_47 + ">>(3) The Commissioner cannot decide the application before the later of the following days "
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'the day stated in a notice given to any party to the application under section 11F or 81Q as the day by which a submission must be given to the Commissioner to be considered in deciding the application')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'the day stated in a notice given to any party to the application under section 11G as the day by which the requirement under the notice must be complied with.')
heading_51 = heading_47 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'The powers of the Commissioner under section 11B do not apply for the purposes of deciding the application.')
heading_52 = heading_47 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'This section does not apply if the Commissioner declines to decide the application under section 11L.')
heading_47 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11I inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>11J. Notice of Commissioners decision"
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'The Commissioner must give notice of the Commissioners decision on an application to each party to the application.')
heading_50 = heading_48 + ">>(2) The notice must state "
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'the decision and')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'the Commissioners reasons for the decision and')
heading_53 = heading_50 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'that, if the party is dissatisfied with the decision, the party may appeal the decision to the Magistrates Court within 7 days after the day on which the notice is given and how the party may start an appeal.')
heading_51 = heading_48 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'If the application is a security bond release application, the Commissioner must give a copy of the notice to the bond administrator.')
heading_48 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11J inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>11K. Commissioner may publish decision and reasons"
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>(1) The Commissioner may publish "
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'the Commissioners decision on an application and')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'the Commissioners reasons for the decision.')
heading_51 = heading_49 + ">>(2) However, a decision or reasons published under subsection (1) must not include information that could identify or lead to the identification of "
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'a party to the application or')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'another individual or')
heading_54 = heading_51 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'the residential premises the subject of the application.')
heading_49 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11K inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]"
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>11L. Commissioner may decline to decide application and refer parties to Magistrates Court"
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>(1) The Commissioner may decline to decide an application if the Commissioner "
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'considers the application cannot be decided on the information available to the Commissioner or')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'is aware that another dispute relating to the residential tenancy agreement is before the Magistrates Court or')
heading_54 = heading_51 + ">>(c) for a security bond release application "
heading_55 = heading_54 + ">>(i) does not have current contact details for 1 or more of the parties to the application or"
heading_56 = heading_55 + ">>(ii) considers the amount in dispute is more than the amount of the security bond"
CONTEXT(heading_56, 'or')
heading_55 = heading_51 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'otherwise considers it is appropriate in all of the circumstances to refer the application to the Magistrates Court.')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>(2) If the Commissioner declines to decide an application, the Commissioner must give each party to the application a notice that states "
heading_53 = heading_52 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'the Commissioner declines to decide the application and')
heading_54 = heading_52 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'the Commissioners reasons for declining and')
heading_55 = heading_52 + ">>(c) that the party may apply to the Magistrates Court under section 15(1A) for relief in relation to the matter the subject of the application."
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'Note for this section  See section 12A in relation to the jurisdiction of the Magistrates Court to hear and determine the application.')
heading_50 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 11L inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 11.]; Division 2  Disputes determined by the Magistrates Court [Heading inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 12.]"
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>12. Terms used; In this Division "
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'prescribed amount means $10 000 or such other amount as may be prescribed')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'prescribed dispute means any matter that may be the subject of an application under this Act, other than an application made under this Act that is, or involves, a claim for an amount over the prescribed amount, but includes an application made under clause 8 of Schedule 1, irrespective of the amount claimed.')
heading_51 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 12 inserted No. 59 of 2004 s. 119 amended No. 11 of 2024 s. 13(1).]"
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>12A. Jurisdiction over prescribed disputes"
heading_53 = heading_52 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'The Magistrates Court has exclusive jurisdiction to hear and determine a prescribed dispute and such disputes are not justiciable by any other court or tribunal.')
heading_54 = heading_52 + ">>(2) A prescribed dispute is a minor case for the purposes of Part 4 of the"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'Magistrates Court (Civil Proceedings) Act 2004 and the jurisdiction conferred by subsection (1) is to be exercised accordingly.')
heading_52 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 12A inserted No. 59 of 2004 s. 119.]"
heading_53 = heading_52 + ">>13. Jurisdiction over other disputes"
heading_54 = heading_53 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'If an application made under this Act is, or involves, a claim for an amount over the prescribed amount, any court that is competent to hear and determine a claim founded on contract for the amount of that claim has jurisdiction to hear and determine the application.')
heading_55 = heading_53 + ">>(2) To the extent that subsection (1) confers jurisdiction on the Magistrates Court, that jurisdiction is not to be exercised in accordance with Part 4 of the"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'Magistrates Court (Civil Proceedings) Act 2004 .')
heading_56 = heading_53 + ">>(3) Despite subsection (2), the parties to an application referred to in subsection (1) in respect of which the Magistrates Court has jurisdiction may consent in writing (which consent is irrevocable) to the proceedings being heard and determined by the Magistrates Court in accordance with Part 4 of the"
CONTEXT(heading_56, 'Magistrates Court (Civil Proceedings) Act 2004 .')
heading_57 = heading_53 + ">>(4) In respect of the hearing and determination of an application referred to in subsection (1) "
heading_58 = heading_57 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_58, 'the practice and procedure applicable in the court dealing with the application shall, subject to subsection (3), apply and this Part (other than this subsection) and regulations made for the purposes of this Part shall not apply but')
heading_59 = heading_57 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_59, 'subject to paragraph (a), this Act shall apply.')
heading_58 = heading_53 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_58, 'If on an application referred to in subsection (1) the plaintiff recovers an amount that is not more than the prescribed amount, the plaintiff shall not be awarded any costs unless the court is satisfied that at the time of making the application there were reasonable grounds for the plaintiff to believe that the plaintiff had a claim for an amount over the prescribed amount.')
heading_53 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 13 inserted No. 59 of 2004 s. 119 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 11.]"
heading_54 = heading_53 + ">>13A. Magistrates Courts jurisdiction"
heading_55 = heading_54 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'For the purpose of exercising the jurisdiction conferred by section 12A and 13, the Magistrates Court is to be constituted by a magistrate.')
heading_56 = heading_54 + ">>(2) Despite subsection (1), a registrar of the Magistrates Court may, subject to the directions of a magistrate, exercise the courts jurisdiction in respect of any application that is to be dealt with in accordance with Part 4 of the; Magistrates Court (Civil Proceedings) Act 2004 if "
heading_57 = heading_56 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_57, 'the application is within a prescribed class of applications and')
heading_58 = heading_56 + ">>(b) either "
heading_59 = heading_58 + ">>(i) the application is not disputed or"
CONTEXT(heading_59, '(ii) a party to the application does not appear.')
heading_57 = heading_54 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_57, 'An application made under this Act to the Magistrates Court shall be made to the court at the place nearest to the place where the premises the subject of the proceedings are situated.')
heading_58 = heading_54 + ">>(4) Subsection (3) does not prevent the Magistrates Court from making an order under the"
CONTEXT(heading_58, 'Magistrates Court (Civil Proceedings) Act 2004 section 22 that proceedings under this Act are to be conducted at another place in the State.')
heading_54 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 13A inserted No. 59 of 2004 s. 119 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 12.]"
heading_55 = heading_54 + ">>13B. Appeals from decisions of registrar"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'A person dissatisfied with a decision of a registrar in respect of a matter on which a registrar has exercised jurisdiction under section 13A(2) may appeal to a magistrate under section 29 of the  Magistrates Court Act 2004 .')
heading_55 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 13B inserted No. 69 of 2006 s. 29.]"
heading_56 = heading_55 + ">>13C. Appeals from decisions of Commissioner"
heading_57 = heading_56 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_57, 'A person who is dissatisfied with the Commissioners decision on an application under section 11I may appeal the decision to the Magistrates Court.')
heading_58 = heading_56 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_58, 'A person may appeal against a decision of the Commissioner on a security bond release application even if the security bond the subject of the application has been paid to 1 or more of the parties to the application under Part 5A Division 2.')
heading_59 = heading_56 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_59, 'The appeal must be started within 7 days after the day on which notice of the Commissioners decision was given to the parties to the application.')
heading_60 = heading_56 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_60, 'A magistrate may extend the period mentioned in subsection (3) and may do so even if the time has elapsed.')
heading_61 = heading_56 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_61, 'The appeal is to be by way of rehearing of the matter the subject of the Commissioners decision.')
heading_62 = heading_56 + ">>(6) The rules of the Magistrates Court apply to the appeal as if the appeal were an appeal of a decision of a registrar under the"
CONTEXT(heading_62, 'Magistrates Court Act 2004 section 29.')
heading_56 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 13C inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 14.]"
heading_57 = heading_56 + ">>14. Time for determination of proceedings"
CONTEXT(heading_57, 'Proceedings under this Act shall be heard and determined wherever practicable within 14 days after they are instituted and, where that is not practicable, as expeditiously as possible.')
heading_58 = heading_56 + ">>15. Applications for relief and orders that may be made"
heading_59 = heading_58 + ">>(1) Where a lessor or tenant under a residential tenancy agreement or a party to an agreement for an option to enter into a residential tenancy agreement claims that a breach of the agreement has occurred or that a dispute has arisen under the agreement, the lessor or tenant may apply for relief to a competent court.  (1A) A lessor or tenant under a residential tenancy agreement who is given a notice under section 11L may apply to the Magistrates Court for relief in relation to the matter the subject of the application to the Commissioner referred to in the notice."
CONTEXT(heading_59, 'Note for this subsection  The Commissioner may decline to decide an application made to the Commissioner under Part III Division 1 and advise the parties that they may apply to the Magistrates Court for relief. See section 11L.')
heading_60 = heading_58 + ">>(2) Upon such an application the court may "
heading_61 = heading_60 + ">>(a) by such order as it considers appropriate in the circumstances "
heading_62 = heading_61 + ">>(i) restrain any action in breach of the agreement or"
heading_63 = heading_62 + ">>(ii) require any action in performance of the agreement"
CONTEXT(heading_63, 'and')
heading_62 = heading_60 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_62, 'order the payment of any amount payable under the agreement and')
heading_63 = heading_60 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_63, 'order the payment of compensation for loss or injury, other than personal injury, caused by any breach of the agreement and')
heading_64 = heading_60 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'authorise payment of the rent under the agreement into the Magistrates Court until the agreement has been performed or any application for compensation has been determined, and order that such rent be paid out towards the cost of remedying the breach or towards the amount of any compensation or otherwise as it considers appropriate and')
heading_65 = heading_60 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_65, 'make such ancillary or incidental order as the court considers appropriate.')
heading_61 = heading_58 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_61, 'The court may make an order under subsection (2)(a) notwithstanding that it provides a remedy in the nature of an injunction or order for specific performance in circumstances in which such remedy would not otherwise be available.')
heading_62 = heading_58 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_62, 'Upon an application with respect to the breach of a residential tenancy agreement, the court shall take into account any previous breaches by the lessor or tenant of the agreement.')
heading_63 = heading_58 + ">>(5) The court may order that a person be joined as a party to the proceedings if the court considers that "
heading_64 = heading_63 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'the person ought to be bound by, or have the benefit of, a decision of the court in the proceedings or')
heading_65 = heading_63 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_65, 'the persons interests are affected by the proceedings or')
heading_66 = heading_63 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'for any other reason it is desirable that the person be joined as a party.')
heading_64 = heading_58 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'The court may make an order under subsection (5) on the application of any person or on its own initiative.')
heading_57 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 15 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 8 and 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120 and 121 No. 60 of 2011 s. 13 and 89 No. 17 of 2014 s. 5 No. 11 of 2024 s. 15(1).]"
heading_58 = heading_57 + ">>16. Enforcement"
heading_59 = heading_58 + ">>(1) A person shall not, without reasonable excuse, fail to comply with an order under section 15(2) other than an order for payment of any amount."
CONTEXT(heading_59, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $10 000.')
heading_60 = heading_58 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_60, 'An order made under this Act by a competent court may be enforced as if it were a judgment of that court.')
heading_58 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 16 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 9 No. 59 of 2004 s. 121 No. 60 of 2011 s. 14 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_59 = heading_58 + ">>17A. Disputes between tenants"
heading_60 = heading_59 + ">>(1) Where 2 or more tenants under a residential tenancy agreement are jointly liable under the agreement to pay an amount to the lessor and one of the tenants (the first tenant"
CONTEXT(heading_60, ') pays another tenants portion of that amount, the first tenant may apply to a competent court for an order that the other tenant pay to the first tenant the other tenants portion.')
heading_61 = heading_59 + ">>(2) The court hearing the application may "
heading_62 = heading_61 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_62, 'make the order referred to in subsection (1) and')
heading_63 = heading_61 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_63, 'order the payment of compensation to the first tenant by the other tenant for loss or injury, other than personal injury, caused by a failure by the other tenant to pay that tenants portion of the amount referred to in subsection (1) and')
heading_64 = heading_61 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'make such ancillary or incidental order as the court considers appropriate.')
heading_59 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 17A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 15.]"
heading_60 = heading_59 + ">>17B. Determination of rights and liabilities after termination of tenants interest on grounds of family violence"
heading_61 = heading_60 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_61, 'A tenant, or former tenant, under a residential tenancy agreement may apply to a competent court for a determination')
heading_62 = heading_60 + ">>(2) When hearing an application under subsection (1) or section 71AE(3), the court "
heading_63 = heading_62 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_63, 'must determine the rights and liabilities of the parties to the agreement, as affected by the termination and')
heading_64 = heading_62 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'may order a party to pay compensation to another party for loss or injury, other than personal injury, relating to the termination.')
heading_63 = heading_60 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_63, 'Without limiting subsection (2), a determination or order under that provision may apportion the disposal of a security bond to the lessor and each tenant or former tenant as appropriate having regard to subsection (4).')
heading_64 = heading_60 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'Despite any law to the contrary, each tenant under a residential tenancy agreement has an equal interest in the security bond in respect of the agreement unless the court in a particular case determines otherwise under this section.')
heading_65 = heading_60 + ">>(5) In making a determination or order under subsection (2), the court must have regard to all of the following principles "
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'that family violence is a fundamental violation of human rights and is unacceptable in any form')
heading_67 = heading_65 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'the need to prevent further victimisation of a person who has experienced family violence through the unjust application of the principle of joint and several liability or the principle of vicarious liability')
heading_68 = heading_65 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'the need to maximise the safety of persons who have experienced family violence by reducing any financial burden arising from the family violence')
heading_69 = heading_65 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'the need to prevent, or reduce to the greatest extent possible, the consequences of family violence')
heading_70 = heading_65 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'the need to protect the wellbeing of children by preventing them from being subjected or exposed to further family violence')
heading_71 = heading_65 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'the need to encourage perpetrators of family violence to accept responsibility for their behaviour and the effect it has on others.')
heading_66 = heading_60 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'Nothing in subsection (2) is to be read as enabling the court to order compensation for early termination of a residential tenancy agreement.')
heading_60 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 17B inserted No. 3 of 2019 s. 5.]"
heading_61 = heading_60 + ">>17. Application to vary or set aside order"
heading_62 = heading_61 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_62, 'A person who is or was a party to any proceedings on an application under this Act may apply to a competent court for an order varying or setting aside an order made in those proceedings if the application was heard in the persons absence.')
heading_63 = heading_61 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_63, 'An application to vary or set aside an order, other than an order under section 84, must be made within 14 days after the making of the order.')
heading_61 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 17 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 121 No. 60 of 2011 s. 16.]"
heading_62 = heading_61 + ">>18. Form of applications and notice of hearing"
heading_63 = heading_62 + ">>(1) Any application under this Act shall "
heading_64 = heading_63 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_64, 'be made in writing in a form approved by the Minister and')
heading_65 = heading_63 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_65, 'be accompanied by the prescribed fee (if any).')
heading_64 = heading_62 + ">>(2) Before a competent court hears an application the court shall "
heading_65 = heading_64 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_65, 'give to the applicant notice in writing setting out the time and place of the hearing and')
heading_66 = heading_64 + ">>(b) give to any other party "
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>(i) notice in writing setting out the time and place of the hearing and"
CONTEXT(heading_67, '(ii) such notice of the nature of the application as is required by rules of court or directed by the court in a particular case.')
heading_62 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 18 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 10 No. 59 of 2004 s. 121.]"
heading_63 = heading_62 + ">>19. Witnesses and inspection of documents"
heading_64 = heading_63 + ">>(1) For the purpose of any proceedings "
heading_65 = heading_64 + ">>(a) a competent court may by summons "
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>(i) require the attendance of any person before the court or"
CONTEXT(heading_66, '(ii) require the production of any books, papers or documents or  (iii) require both such attendance and production')
heading_66 = heading_64 + ">>(b) a competent court may "
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>(i) inspect any books, papers or documents produced, retain them for such reasonable period as it thinks fit, and make copies of any of them, or of any of their contents"
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_68, '(ii) require any person appearing before it to make an oath or affirmation that the person will truly answer any relevant question put to the person by the court or any person appearing before the court')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_69, '(iii) require any person appearing before it (whether the person has been summoned to appear or not) to answer any relevant question put to the person by the court or any person appearing before the court.')
heading_65 = heading_63 + ">>(2) A person shall not "
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'without reasonable excuse fail to comply with the requirements of a summons served on the person under subsection (1) or')
heading_67 = heading_65 + ">>(b) refuse or fail to comply with a requirement under subsection (1)."
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $10 000.')
heading_63 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 19 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 11 and 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(2) and 121 No. 60 of 2011 s. 17 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_64 = heading_63 + ">>20. General powers in proceedings; A competent court hearing any application may "
heading_65 = heading_64 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_65, 'hear the application in such manner as it considers best suited to the purposes of this Act and')
heading_66 = heading_64 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_66, 'decline to entertain the application if it considers that the application is frivolous and')
heading_67 = heading_64 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_67, 'proceed to hear and determine the application in the absence of any party thereto and')
heading_68 = heading_64 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'where a person contravenes subsection (2) of section 19, issue a warrant to bring the person before a competent court for the purposes of subsection (1) of that section and')
heading_69 = heading_64 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'order the refund to a person of a fee paid under section 18(1) by that person and')
heading_70 = heading_64 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'extend or shorten any period prescribed by or under this Act within which any action must be taken, such power to extend a period being exercisable notwithstanding that that period has expired and')
heading_71 = heading_64 + ">>g"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'vary or set aside any order where it considers there are proper grounds for doing so and')
heading_72 = heading_64 + ">>h"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'adjourn the hearing to any time or place or to a time and place to be fixed and')
heading_73 = heading_64 + ">>i"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'allow the amendment of the application and')
heading_74 = heading_64 + ">>j"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'hear the application jointly with any other application and')
heading_75 = heading_64 + ">>k"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'receive in evidence any transcript of evidence in proceedings before the court or any other court and draw any conclusions of fact therefrom that it considers proper and')
heading_76 = heading_64 + ">>l"
CONTEXT(heading_76, 'adopt, as it considers proper, any findings, decision or judgment of the court or any other court that may be relevant to the proceedings and')
heading_77 = heading_64 + ">>m"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'generally give all such directions and do all such things that it thinks necessary or expedient in the proceedings.')
heading_64 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 20 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 12 and 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(1) and (2) and 121 No. 60 of 2011 s. 18.]"
heading_65 = heading_64 + ">>21. Evidence"
CONTEXT(heading_65, 'In any proceedings on an application under this Act, a competent court shall not be bound by the rules of evidence but may inform itself upon any matter relating to the proceedings in such manner as it thinks fit.')
heading_65 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 21 inserted No. 59 of 2004 s. 121.]"
heading_66 = heading_65 + ">>22. Presentation of cases   (1A) In this section "
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>proceedings means proceedings under this Act other than proceedings for an offence against this Act."
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'Except as provided in this section, a party to any proceedings shall present the partys own case and not be represented or assisted in the presentation of the partys case by another person.')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(2) A party to any proceedings may be represented or assisted by an agent in the presentation of the partys case if "
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>(a) the agent is authorised by the party to do so and is "
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>(i) the property manager of the premises the subject of the proceedings or"
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>(ii) employed or engaged by a non-profit association or similar body to act as an advocate for tenants or lessors in proceedings"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'or')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(b) the court makes an order under subsection (3C).  (3A) The authorisation mentioned in subsection (2)(a) must "
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'be made in writing in a form approved by the Minister and')
heading_73 = heading_71 + ">>(b) be lodged with the court together with the application, or response to the application, to which the proceedings relate, as the case requires.  (3B) Without limiting how an agent representing or assisting a party under subsection (2)(a) may represent or assist the party, the agent may initiate proceedings on behalf of the party.   (3C) The court may order that a party to proceedings may be represented or assisted by an agent in the presentation of the partys case if the court hearing the proceeding is satisfied that "
heading_74 = heading_73 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'the party is unable to appear personally or conduct the proceedings on the partys own behalf and')
heading_75 = heading_73 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'another party to the proceedings will not be disadvantaged by the party being represented by, or assisted by, the agent.')
heading_70 = heading_67 + ">>(3) All or any of the parties to any proceedings may be represented by legal practitioners if any of the following applies "
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'all the parties agree and the court hearing the proceedings is satisfied that any party who is not so represented will not be unfairly disadvantaged')
heading_72 = heading_70 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'one of the parties is a legally qualified person')
heading_73 = heading_70 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'one of the parties is a body corporate and any other party elects to be so represented')
heading_74 = heading_70 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'the court is satisfied that one of the parties is unable to conduct the proceedings without representation by a legal practitioner')
heading_75 = heading_70 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'the proceedings are instituted or defended, or the conduct thereof has been assumed, by the Commissioner.')
heading_71 = heading_67 + ">>(4) This section does not prevent "
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'a body corporate from being represented by an officer or employee of the body corporate (not being a legally qualified person) authorised to conduct the proceedings on its behalf (whether or not the officer or employee is remunerated by the body corporate for representing it in the proceedings) or')
heading_73 = heading_71 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'a person from acting as an interpreter for a party, if the persons fee does not exceed an amount fixed by the court at the hearing.')
heading_72 = heading_67 + ">>(5) A person shall not demand or receive any fee or reward for representing or assisting a party to proceedings unless "
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'the person is a legal practitioner or')
heading_74 = heading_72 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'where the party is a body corporate, the person is an officer or employee of the body corporate representing it under subsection (4) or')
heading_75 = heading_72 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'where the party is a lessor, the person is a property manager of the premises the subject of the proceedings.')
heading_73 = heading_67 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'In this section')
heading_68 = heading_66 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_68, 'agent means any person who is not a legally qualified person')
heading_69 = heading_66 + ">>content3"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'legally qualified person means a lawyer or a person who holds or has held legal qualifications under the laws of this State or any other place.')
heading_66 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 22 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 65 of 2003 s. 61 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(3) No. 21 of 2008 s. 698 No. 60 of 2011 s. 19 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25 No. 25 of 2019 s. 65 No. 9 of 2022 s. 424.]"
heading_67 = heading_66 + ">>23. Settlement by conciliation"
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>(1) If before or during the hearing of any proceedings it appears to a competent court either from the nature of the case or from the attitude of the parties that there is a reasonable possibility of matters in dispute between the parties being settled by conciliation, it may "
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'interview the parties in private (either with or without any person who may be representing any of them or assisting any of them in the presentation of the partys case) and')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'endeavour to bring about a settlement of the proceedings on terms that are fair to all parties.')
heading_69 = heading_67 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_69, 'Nothing said or done in the course of any attempt to settle proceedings under this section shall subsequently be given in evidence in any proceedings nor shall the judicial officer who presided be thereby disqualified from hearing or continuing to hear the proceedings if the judicial officer thinks fit to do so.')
heading_70 = heading_67 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'Where proceedings are settled under this section, the court may embody the terms of the settlement in an order.')
heading_71 = heading_67 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'The order is valid despite any inconsistency with Part IV or V.')
heading_67 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 23 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(2) and (3) and 121 No. 60 of 2011 s. 20.]"
heading_68 = heading_67 + ">>24. Costs"
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>(1) A competent court hearing proceedings shall not award costs, unless "
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'all parties to the proceedings were represented by legal practitioners or')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'it is of the opinion that there are special circumstances justifying the award of costs.')
heading_70 = heading_68 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'Where a party to the proceedings has paid a fee under section 18(1), nothing in subsection (1) is to be taken to prevent a court making an order which requires any other party to the proceedings to pay to the first-mentioned party the amount of that fee.')
heading_68 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 24 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 1995 s. 45 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(2) and (3) and 121 No. 9 of 2022 s. 424.]"
heading_69 = heading_68 + ">>25. Reservation of question of law"
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_70, 'A competent court hearing proceedings may reserve any question of law for the decision of the Supreme Court.')
heading_71 = heading_69 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'Any costs arising from the reservation of any question under this section, including any costs incurred by the parties to the proceedings, shall be charged to the Consolidated Account and this subsection, without any further appropriation, shall be sufficient authority for any such payment.')
heading_69 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 25 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 6 of 1993 s. 11 No. 59 of 1995 s. 56 No. 59 of 2004 s. 121 No. 77 of 2006 s. 4.]"
heading_70 = heading_69 + ">>26. Finality of proceedings"
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_71, 'An order made by a court under this Act is final and binding on all parties to the proceedings in which the order is made and on all persons who under this Act could have become entitled to be joined as a party to the proceeding in which the order is made, and no appeal shall lie in respect thereof.')
heading_72 = heading_70 + ">>(2) No declaratory judgment shall be given and no order shall be made under section 36 of the"
CONTEXT(heading_72, 'Magistrates Court Act 2004 in respect of proceedings taken or to be taken under this Act in the Magistrates Court or any order made in such proceedings by that court, unless the Supreme Court is satisfied that the Magistrates Court had or has no jurisdiction conferred by or under this Act in respect of the proceedings or that a party to the proceedings has been denied natural justice.')
heading_73 = heading_70 + ">>(3) This section applies despite Part 7 of the"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'Magistrates Court (Civil Proceedings) Act 2004 .')
heading_70 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 26 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 13 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(3) and 121 No. 69 of 2006 s. 30.]; Division 3  Retaliatory action taken by lessor  [Heading inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 17.]"
heading_71 = heading_70 + ">>26A. Retaliatory action; A lessor takes retaliatory action against a tenant in relation to a matter referred to in section 26B(2)(a), (b) or (c) if the lessor "
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>(a) takes any of the following action "
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>(i) gives the tenant a notice claiming the tenant has breached the residential tenancy agreement, other than by failing to pay rent, and requiring the tenant to remedy the breach"
heading_74 = heading_73 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_74, '(ii) increases the rent payable under the residential tenancy agreement')
heading_75 = heading_73 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_75, '(iii) takes action to terminate the residential tenancy agreement')
heading_76 = heading_73 + ">>(iv) at the end of the current residential tenancy agreement, refuses to enter into a further residential tenancy agreement with the tenant"
CONTEXT(heading_76, 'and')
heading_73 = heading_71 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'is motivated to take the action, wholly or partly, by the matter arising.')
heading_71 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 26A inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 17.]"
heading_72 = heading_71 + ">>26B. Retaliatory action taken by lessor"
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>(1) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_73, 'representative entity means an entity that has a purpose of providing advice or support to tenants.')
heading_74 = heading_72 + ">>(2) This section applies if a tenant reasonably believes the lessor took retaliatory action against the tenant after any of the following matters arose "
heading_75 = heading_74 + ">>(a) the tenant, or a representative entity, takes action to enforce the tenants rights, including, for example, by "
heading_76 = heading_75 + ">>(i) asking for repairs or maintenance to the premises or"
CONTEXT(heading_76, '(ii) giving the lessor a notice claiming the lessor has breached the residential tenancy agreement and requiring the lessor to remedy the breach or  (iii) requiring the lessor to reimburse the tenant for a reasonable expense properly incurred by the tenant for urgent repairs or  (iv) applying to a competent court for an order under this Act')
heading_76 = heading_74 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_76, 'the lessor or lessors agent knows that the tenant or a representative entity has complained to the Commissioner or another government entity about an act')
heading_77 = heading_74 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'an order of a competent court is in force in relation to the lessor and tenant.')
heading_75 = heading_72 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'The tenant may apply to a competent court for relief in relation to the lessors action alleged by the tenant to be retaliatory action.')
heading_76 = heading_72 + ">>(4) The court hearing the application may, if the court is satisfied the lessors action was likely to have been retaliatory action for a matter mentioned in subsection (2)(a), (b) or (c), make any order the court considers appropriate, including, for example "
heading_77 = heading_76 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'an order setting aside the lessors action and')
heading_78 = heading_76 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_78, 'an order that the lessor pay compensation to the tenant for loss or injury, other than personal injury, caused by the lessors action.')
heading_72 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 26B inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 17.]; Part IV  Residential tenancy agreements  [Heading inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 21.]; Division 1A  Form of residential tenancy agreement and associated documents  [Heading inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 22.]"
heading_73 = heading_72 + ">>27A. Written residential tenancy agreement to be in approved form"
heading_74 = heading_73 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_74, 'A lessor or property manager must ensure a written residential tenancy agreement entered into by the lessor is in the approved form.')
heading_75 = heading_73 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_75, 'Penalty a fine of $5 000.')
heading_73 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 27A inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 18.]"
heading_74 = heading_73 + ">>27B. Information to be given to tenant by lessor"
heading_75 = heading_74 + ">>A lessor or property manager must give a copy of the information (if any) prescribed for the purposes of this section to each tenant "
heading_76 = heading_75 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_76, 'in the case of a written residential tenancy agreement, at the time of entering into the agreement or')
heading_77 = heading_75 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'in any other case, within 14 days after the tenant has taken possession of the residential premises.')
heading_76 = heading_74 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_76, 'Penalty a fine of $5 000.')
heading_74 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 27B inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 22 amended No. 11 of 2024 s. 19.]"
heading_75 = heading_74 + ">>27C. Property condition report at start and end of tenancy"
heading_76 = heading_75 + ">>(1) A lessor or property manager must, within 7 days after a tenant has entered into occupation of residential premises under a residential tenancy agreement "
heading_77 = heading_76 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'prepare a report describing the condition of the premises and')
heading_78 = heading_76 + ">>(b) provide 2 copies of the report to the tenant."
CONTEXT(heading_78, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_77 = heading_75 + ">>(2) A tenant given copies of a report under subsection (1)(b) who disagrees with any information in the report must, within 7 days of receiving the copies "
heading_78 = heading_77 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_78, 'mark a copy in a manner that shows the information with which the tenant disagrees and')
heading_79 = heading_77 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_79, 'give the copy back to the lessor or property manager, as the case requires.')
heading_78 = heading_75 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_78, 'If the tenant does not give a copy of the report back to the lessor or property manager under subsection (2), the tenant is to be taken to accept the report as a true and accurate description of the condition of the residential premises.')
heading_79 = heading_75 + ">>(4) A lessor or property manager must, as soon as practicable, and in any event within 14 days, after the termination of a tenancy or tenants interest in a residential tenancy agreement "
heading_80 = heading_79 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_80, 'conduct an inspection of the residential premises and')
heading_81 = heading_79 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_81, 'prepare a final report describing the condition of the premises and')
heading_82 = heading_79 + ">>(c) provide a copy of the report to the tenant.; Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.  (4A) A lessor or property manager is taken to comply with subsection (4) if, before the termination of a tenants interest, the lessor or property manager "
heading_83 = heading_82 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_83, 'enters residential premises under section 46(6B) and')
heading_84 = heading_82 + ">>(b) in relation to that entry "
heading_85 = heading_84 + ">>(i) conducts an inspection of the premises and"
CONTEXT(heading_85, '(ii) prepares a report describing the condition of the premises and   (iii) provides a copy of the report to the tenant.')
heading_80 = heading_75 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_80, 'The tenant is to be given a reasonable opportunity to be present at the inspection conducted under subsection (4)(a) or (4A)(a).')
heading_81 = heading_75 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_81, 'The regulations may prescribe information that must be included in a property condition report.')
heading_75 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 27C inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 22 amended No. 3 of 2019 s. 6 and 25 No. 11 of 2024 s. 20.]; Division 1  Rent and security bonds"
heading_76 = heading_75 + ">>27. Restriction on consideration for tenancy agreement"
heading_77 = heading_76 + ">>(1) A person must not require or receive from a tenant any monetary amount for or in relation to a residential tenancy agreement other than rent and a security bond."
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_78 = heading_76 + ">>(2) Subsection (1) does not apply to "
heading_79 = heading_78 + ">>(a) any amount, not exceeding a prescribed amount, required or received as consideration for an option to enter into a residential tenancy agreement if "
heading_80 = heading_79 + ">>(i) upon the option being exercised, the amount is refunded in cash or applied towards the rent payable under the agreement or"
heading_81 = heading_80 + ">>(ii) upon the option being refused, and within 7 days of the decision to refuse the option, the amount is refunded in cash, by electronic means or in any other prescribed way"
CONTEXT(heading_81, 'and')
heading_80 = heading_78 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_80, 'any amount that the lessor is authorised by any other provision of this Act to require or receive and')
heading_76 = heading_27 + ">>[(c) deleted]"
heading_77 = heading_76 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_77, 'any other payment of a prescribed class.')
heading_77 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 27 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 46 and 55 No. 60 of 2011 s. 23 and 89 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25 No. 11 of 2024 s. 21.]   27AA. Residential tenancy must be offered for rent at fixed amount"
heading_78 = heading_77 + ">>(1) A person must not advertise or otherwise offer a tenancy for residential premises unless "
heading_79 = heading_78 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_79, 'the amount of rent stated in the advertisement or offer is a fixed amount or')
heading_80 = heading_78 + ">>(b) the advertisement or offer states that the amount of rent is calculated by reference to the tenants income."
CONTEXT(heading_80, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $10 000.')
heading_79 = heading_77 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_79, 'A person does not commit an offence against subsection (1) if the person places a sign advertising or offering residential premises for rent at or near the premises and the sign does not state an amount of rent for the premises.')
heading_80 = heading_77 + ">>(3) A person must not solicit or otherwise invite a person to make an offer to become a tenant of residential premises at a rent higher than the amount advertised as the rent for the premises."
CONTEXT(heading_80, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $10 000.')
heading_78 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 27AA inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 22.]"
heading_79 = heading_78 + ">>28. Rent in advance"
heading_80 = heading_79 + ">>(1) A person must not require before or during the first 2 weeks of the tenancy under a residential tenancy agreement as rent under the agreement an amount exceeding 2 weeks rent."
CONTEXT(heading_80, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_81 = heading_79 + ">>(2) A person must not require any payment of rent (other than the first payment) under a residential tenancy agreement "
heading_82 = heading_81 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_82, 'until the period of the tenancy in respect of which any previous payment has been made has elapsed and')
heading_83 = heading_81 + ">>(b) unless the amount does not exceed 2 weeks rent."
CONTEXT(heading_83, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_79 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 28 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 55 No. 60 of 2011 s. 24 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25 No. 11 of 2024 s. 23.]"
heading_80 = heading_79 + ">>29. Security bonds   (1A) In this section, unless the contrary intention appears ; security bond includes an instalment of a security bond."
heading_81 = heading_80 + ">>(1) A person shall not "
heading_82 = heading_81 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_82, 'require the payment of, or receive, more than one security bond in relation to any residential tenancy agreement or')
heading_83 = heading_81 + ">>(b) require the payment of, or receive, a security bond of an amount exceeding in the aggregate "
heading_84 = heading_83 + ">>(i) 4 weeks rent under the residential tenancy agreement in relation to which it is required or received and"
heading_85 = heading_84 + ">>(ii) if the tenant is permitted to keep on the premises any pet capable of carrying parasites that can affect humans  a prescribed amount to meet the cost of any fumigation of the premises that may be required on the termination of the tenancy."
CONTEXT(heading_85, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.  (2A) Subsection (1)(a) does not prevent a person from receiving a security bond in instalments.')
heading_82 = heading_80 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_82, 'Subsection (1)(b) does not apply in relation to a residential tenancy agreement where the weekly rate of rent payable under the agreement exceeds a prescribed amount.')
heading_83 = heading_80 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_83, 'Where, during the period of 6 months after the day on which the tenancy under a residential tenancy agreement commenced, the rent payable under the agreement decreases or is decreased, the amount paid in excess of the lower or, as the case may be, lowest rate of rent payable under the agreement during that period, together with the amount (if any) allowed by subsection (1)(b)(ii), shall be deemed to have been paid as a security bond.')
heading_84 = heading_80 + ">>(4) A person who receives a security bond paid in relation to a residential tenancy agreement "
heading_85 = heading_84 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_85, 'shall forthwith give or cause to be given to the person paying the bond a receipt specifying the date on which the bond was received, the name of the person paying the bond, the amount paid and the premises in respect of which it is paid and')
heading_86 = heading_84 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_86, 'shall pay the amount of the bond to the bond administrator in accordance with Schedule 1 clause 5A and')
heading_87 = heading_84 + ">>(c) shall, at the time of making the payment referred to in paragraph (b), lodge with the bond administrator a record in a form approved by the Minister relating to the payment."
CONTEXT(heading_87, '[(d) deleted]  Penalty for this subsection a fine of $20 000.')
heading_80 = heading_27 + ">>[(5) deleted]"
heading_81 = heading_80 + ">>(6) A person shall not make an entry in a record referred to in subsection (4)(c) that the person knows is false or misleading in a material particular."
CONTEXT(heading_81, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_82 = heading_80 + ">>(7)"
CONTEXT(heading_82, 'The bond administrator must pay the amount of the security bond in accordance with Schedule 1 clause 5.')
heading_83 = heading_80 + ">>(8) A lessor and property manager must ensure that an application form referred to in Schedule 1 clause 5(1)(a) is not signed by a tenant unless "
heading_84 = heading_83 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_84, 'the residential tenancy agreement to which the security bond relates has terminated and')
heading_85 = heading_83 + ">>(b) any amount of the security bond to be paid to the lessor or tenant is stipulated on the form."
CONTEXT(heading_85, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_84 = heading_80 + ">>(9)"
CONTEXT(heading_84, 'Nothing in subsection (1)(a) prevents the lessor from requiring further payment from a remaining tenant towards the security bond in order to cover the disposal of a former tenants portion of the security bond under section 17B(3).')
heading_81 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 29 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 47 and 55 No. 69 of 2006 s. 31 No. 60 of 2011 s. 25 No. 18 of 2013 s. 62 No. 3 of 2019 .s 7 and 25 No. 11 of 2024 s. 24(1).]  ["
heading_82 = heading_81 + ">>29A.; Deleted No. 60 of 2011 s. 26.]"
heading_83 = heading_82 + ">>30. Variation of rent (except where calculated by reference to tenants income)"
heading_84 = heading_83 + ">>(1) Subject to this section and except where rent payable under a residential tenancy agreement is calculated by reference to the tenants income, the rent payable under a residential tenancy agreement may be increased by the lessor by written notice to the tenant, in the approved form, specifying the amount of the increased rent and the day as from which the increased rent becomes payable, being a day "
heading_85 = heading_84 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_85, 'not less than 60 days after the day on which the notice is given and')
heading_86 = heading_84 + ">>(b) not less than 12 months after the day on which the tenancy commenced, or, if the rent has been increased under this section, the day on which it was last so increased,"
CONTEXT(heading_86, 'but otherwise the rent shall not increase or be increased.')
heading_85 = heading_83 + ">>(2) The right of the lessor to increase rent in accordance with subsection (1) "
heading_86 = heading_85 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_86, 'is not exercisable in relation to a residential tenancy agreement that creates a tenancy for a fixed term during the currency of that term unless the amount of the increase, or the method of calculating the amount of the increase, is set out in the agreement and')
heading_87 = heading_85 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_87, 'in any case, may be excluded or limited by agreement between the lessor and the tenant.')
heading_86 = heading_83 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_86, 'A notice of increase of rent that has been given in accordance with this section and that has not been withdrawn by the lessor varies the residential tenancy agreement to the effect that the increased rent specified in the notice is payable under the agreement as from the day specified in the notice.')
heading_82 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 30 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 27, 88 and 89 No. 11 of 2024 s. 25.]"
heading_83 = heading_82 + ">>31A. Variation of rent where calculated by reference to tenants income"
heading_84 = heading_83 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_84, 'Where rent payable under a residential tenancy agreement is calculated by reference to the tenants income, the method by which the rent is calculated by reference to that income may be changed by the lessor in accordance with this section but otherwise the rent must not increase or be increased.')
heading_85 = heading_83 + ">>(2) The method may be changed by notice in writing to the tenant, in the approved form, specifying "
heading_86 = heading_85 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_86, 'the change to the method and')
heading_87 = heading_85 + ">>(b) the day as from which the change will take effect, being a day "
heading_88 = heading_87 + ">>(i) not less than 60 days after the day on which the notice is given and"
CONTEXT(heading_88, '(ii) not less than 12 months after the day on which the tenancy commenced, or, if the means of calculating rent has been changed under this section, the day on which it was last so changed.')
heading_83 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 31A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 28 amended No. 11 of 2024 s. 26.]"
heading_84 = heading_83 + ">>31B. When residential tenancy agreement is continuation of existing residential tenancy agreement"
heading_85 = heading_84 + ">>(1) This section applies for the purposes of working out "
heading_86 = heading_85 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_86, 'when the rent payable under a residential tenancy agreement was last increased under section 30 or')
heading_87 = heading_85 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_87, 'when the means of calculating rent under a residential tenancy agreement was last changed under section 31A.')
heading_86 = heading_84 + ">>(2) A residential tenancy agreement (the continuing agreement"
heading_87 = heading_86 + ">>) is taken to be a continuation of another residential tenancy agreement (the existing agreement ) if the continuing agreement "
heading_88 = heading_87 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_88, 'is between the same parties as the existing agreement and')
heading_89 = heading_87 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_89, 'is for the same residential premises as the existing agreement and')
heading_90 = heading_87 + ">>(c) starts immediately after the end of the term of the existing agreement."
CONTEXT(heading_90, 'Note for this subsection  See also section 76C for the circumstances in which a residential tenancy agreement that creates a tenancy for a fixed term continues as a periodic tenancy.')
heading_87 = heading_84 + ">>(3) For subsection (2)(a), the existing agreement and the continuing agreement are between the same parties if "
heading_88 = heading_87 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_88, 'the lessor is the same under both agreements and')
heading_89 = heading_87 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_89, 'the tenant, or at least 1 co-tenant, is the same under both agreements.')
heading_84 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 31B inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 27.]"
heading_85 = heading_84 + ">>31. Increase in security bond"
heading_86 = heading_85 + ">>(1) The amount of the security bond for a residential tenancy agreement can only be increased in accordance with this section.  (1A) If a notice of increase in rent is given under section 30 or 31A in relation to a residential tenancy agreement, the lessor may increase the amount of the security bond for the agreement by giving the tenant a written notice that states "
heading_87 = heading_86 + ">>(a) the amount by which the security bond is increased (the additional amount"
CONTEXT(heading_87, ') and')
heading_88 = heading_86 + ">>(b) the day on which the additional amount is payable.  (1B) For the purposes of subsection (1A)(b), the day on which the additional amount is payable cannot be a day "
heading_89 = heading_88 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_89, 'earlier than 60 days after the day on which the notice under subsection (1A) is given or')
heading_90 = heading_88 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_90, 'before the rent increase the subject of the notice given under section 30 or 31A takes effect.  (1C) Despite section 29(1)(b), a person may receive, but may not require, the payment of the additional amount before the day on which the additional amount is payable.')
heading_87 = heading_85 + ">>(2) The amount of a security bond may not be increased under this section to an amount that would exceed the aggregate of "
heading_88 = heading_87 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_88, '4 weeks rent under the residential tenancy agreement at the time at which the amount of the increase would be payable and')
heading_89 = heading_87 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_89, 'any amount provided for by section 29(1)(b)(ii).')
heading_88 = heading_85 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_88, 'A notice of increase of the amount of a security bond that has been given in accordance with this section and that has not been withdrawn by the lessor varies the residential tenancy agreement to the effect that the amount of the increase specified in the notice is payable under the agreement on the day specified in the notice.')
heading_89 = heading_85 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_89, 'Section 29(4) and (5) apply to an amount paid under this section.')
heading_85 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 31 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 29 and 89 No. 23 of 2014 s. 89 No. 11 of 2024 s. 28.]"
heading_86 = heading_85 + ">>32. Limitation of excessive rents in certain circumstances"
heading_87 = heading_86 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_87, 'A tenant under a residential tenancy agreement may apply to a competent court for an order declaring that the rent payable in respect of the premises is excessive.')
heading_88 = heading_86 + ">>(2) An application under subsection (1) must be made not more than 30 days, or any greater period as the court thinks fit having regard to the justice and merits of the case, after "
heading_89 = heading_88 + ">>(a) the tenant has received notice of "
heading_90 = heading_89 + ">>(i) an increase in the rent payable or"
heading_91 = heading_90 + ">>(ii) a change in the method of calculating rent that results in an increase in the rent payable"
CONTEXT(heading_91, 'or')
heading_90 = heading_88 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_90, 'there has been, without any default on the part of the tenant, a significant reduction in the chattels or facilities provided with the premises.')
heading_89 = heading_86 + ">>(3) The court shall, in determining whether or not the rent payable in respect of the premises is excessive, have regard to "
heading_90 = heading_89 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_90, 'the general level of rents for comparable premises in the locality or a similar locality and')
heading_91 = heading_89 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_91, 'the estimated capital value of the premises at the date of the application and')
heading_92 = heading_89 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_92, 'the amount of the outgoings in respect of the premises required to be borne by the lessor under the agreement and')
heading_93 = heading_89 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_93, 'the estimated cost of any services provided by the lessor or tenant under the agreement and')
heading_94 = heading_89 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_94, 'the value and nature of the chattels provided with the premises for use by the tenant and')
heading_95 = heading_89 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_95, 'the accommodation and amenities provided in the premises and the state of repair and general condition thereof and')
heading_96 = heading_89 + ">>g"
