heading_126 = heading_124 + ">>(2) The Commissioner must "
heading_127 = heading_126 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_127, 'if satisfied the lessors refusal is not permitted under section 50Q or 50R  order the lessor to consent to the tenants request or')
heading_128 = heading_126 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_128, 'if satisfied any of the grounds referred to in section 50S(3) apply  approve the lessors refusal of the tenants request or')
heading_129 = heading_126 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_129, 'otherwise  refuse the tenants application.')
heading_127 = heading_124 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_127, 'If the Commissioner makes an order under subsection (2)(a), the Commissioner may also order that the lessors consent is subject to stated conditions.')
heading_124 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50U inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]"
heading_125 = heading_124 + ">>50V. Tenants application for order that conditions imposed on consent are unreasonable"
heading_126 = heading_125 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_126, 'A tenant may apply to the Commissioner for an order that a condition imposed by the lessor on the lessors consent for the tenant to make a minor modification is unreasonable.')
heading_127 = heading_125 + ">>(2) The Commissioner must "
heading_128 = heading_127 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_128, 'if satisfied the condition is unreasonable  approve the tenants application and order that the condition is unreasonable or')
heading_129 = heading_127 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_129, 'if satisfied the condition is reasonable  refuse the tenants application and order that the condition is reasonable or')
heading_130 = heading_127 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_130, 'order that the condition imposed by the lessor be modified in a stated way.')
heading_128 = heading_125 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_128, 'If the Commissioner orders that the condition is unreasonable, the lessors consent to make the minor modification is no longer subject to the condition.')
heading_125 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50V inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]; Subdivision 4  Other modifications  [Heading inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]"
heading_126 = heading_125 + ">>50W. When tenant may make other modifications to premises"
heading_127 = heading_126 + ">>(1) In this section ; major modification, in relation to residential premises, means a modification to the premises other than "
heading_128 = heading_127 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_128, 'a furniture safety modification or')
heading_129 = heading_127 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_129, 'a prescribed modification mentioned in section 50M or')
heading_130 = heading_127 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_130, 'a minor modification.')
heading_128 = heading_126 + ">>(2) A residential tenancy agreement may provide that "
heading_129 = heading_128 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_129, 'a tenant may make a modification to the premises stated in the agreement without the lessors consent or')
heading_130 = heading_128 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_130, 'a tenant may make a major modification to the premises with the lessors consent or')
heading_131 = heading_128 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'a tenant must not make major modifications to the premises.')
heading_129 = heading_126 + ">>(3) If a residential tenancy agreement includes a provision referred to in subsection (2)(a), it is also a term of the agreement that, before making the stated modification to the premises, the tenant must give the lessor written notice "
heading_130 = heading_129 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_130, 'stating that the tenant intends to make the modification and')
heading_131 = heading_129 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'describing the intended modification.')
heading_130 = heading_126 + ">>(4) If a residential tenancy agreement includes a provision referred to subsection (2)(b), it is also a term of the agreement that "
heading_131 = heading_130 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'the lessor must not unreasonably refuse the tenants request for consent to make a major modification to the premises and')
heading_132 = heading_130 + ">>(b) the making of a major modification is subject to any reasonable conditions of the lessors approval for the tenant to make the major modification."
CONTEXT(heading_132, 'Note for this section  See Subdivision 5 for the responsibilities of a tenant who makes a modification to premises.')
heading_126 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50W inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]"
heading_127 = heading_126 + ">>50X. Lessor may make modification to premises"
heading_128 = heading_127 + ">>(1) It is a term of every residential tenancy agreement that "
heading_129 = heading_128 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_129, 'the lessor may make a modification to the premises, but only with the consent of the tenant and')
heading_130 = heading_128 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_130, 'the tenant must not unreasonably refuse the lessors request for consent.')
heading_129 = heading_127 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_129, 'The tenants approval for the lessor to make a modification may be subject to reasonable conditions about the lessors entry of the premises to make or inspect the modification, including the day or time of the entry.')
heading_130 = heading_127 + ">>(3) Section 46(2)(e) applies for the purposes of the lessor making the modification to the premises "
heading_131 = heading_130 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'as if a reference in that section to necessary repairs to or maintenance of the premises were a reference to the modification and')
heading_132 = heading_130 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_132, 'subject to a reasonable condition imposed on the entry under subsection (2).')
heading_127 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50X inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]"
heading_128 = heading_127 + ">>50Y. Request for approval to make modification"
heading_129 = heading_128 + ">>(1) A tenant may ask the lessor (the consenting party"
CONTEXT(heading_129, ') for consent to make a major modification to premises.')
heading_130 = heading_128 + ">>(2) A lessor may ask the tenant (also the consenting party"
CONTEXT(heading_130, ') for consent to make a modification to premises.')
heading_131 = heading_128 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'The request must be in the approved form.')
heading_132 = heading_128 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_132, 'The consenting party must respond to the request within 28 days after the day on which the request is received.')
heading_133 = heading_128 + ">>(5) The consenting partys response must be in writing and state "
heading_134 = heading_133 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'whether the consenting party approves or refuses the request and')
heading_135 = heading_133 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_135, 'if the consenting party approves the request subject to conditions  the conditions of the approval and')
heading_136 = heading_133 + ">>(c) if the consenting party refuses the request "
heading_137 = heading_136 + ">>(i) the grounds for the refusal and"
CONTEXT(heading_137, '(ii) the reasons for the refusal.')
heading_134 = heading_128 + ">>(6)"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'The consenting party is taken to approve the request if the consenting party does not comply with subsection (4).')
heading_128 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50Y inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]"
heading_129 = heading_128 + ">>50Z. Refusal of consent to modification needed for disability access prohibited; The lessor must not refuse a tenants request for consent to make a major modification to premises that is reasonably required to enable a person with disability to access and use the premises if refusing consent would be unlawful under "
heading_130 = heading_129 + ">>(a) the"
heading_131 = heading_130 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'Equal Opportunity Act 1984 section 66L(2)(d) or')
heading_131 = heading_129 + ">>(b) the"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'Disability Discrimination Act 1992 (Commonwealth) section 25(2)(d).')
heading_129 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50Z inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]; Subdivision 5  Tenants responsibilities in relation to modifications to premises  [Heading inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]  50ZA. Purpose of Subdivision  The matters stated in this Subdivision "
heading_130 = heading_129 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_130, 'are terms of every residential tenancy agreement and')
heading_131 = heading_129 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_131, 'apply if a tenant makes a modification to the residential premises.')
heading_130 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50ZA inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]  50ZB. Tenant bears costs of modification and responsibility for repairs"
heading_131 = heading_130 + ">>(1) The tenant must bear the costs of "
heading_132 = heading_131 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_132, 'making the modification to the residential premises and')
heading_133 = heading_131 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_133, 'removing the modification and restoring the premises to their original condition as required under section 50ZD.')
heading_132 = heading_130 + ">>(2) The tenant is responsible for maintaining the modification to the premises in a reasonable state of repair.; [Section 5ZB inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]  50ZC. Modification to have regard to age and character of premises  The tenant must ensure the modification is made in a way that "
heading_133 = heading_132 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_133, 'has regard to the age and character of the premises and')
heading_134 = heading_132 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'complies with any written law and')
heading_135 = heading_132 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_135, 'if the premises are a lot in a community titles scheme or strata titles scheme  complies with the scheme by-laws.')
heading_131 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50ZC inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]  50ZD. Tenant must remove modification and restore premises"
heading_132 = heading_131 + ">>(1) Unless the lessor agrees otherwise in writing, when the tenant vacates the premises at the end of the residential tenancy agreement, the tenant must either "
heading_133 = heading_132 + ">>(a) do the following "
heading_134 = heading_133 + ">>(i) if the modification included attaching a thing to the premises  remove the attached thing"
heading_135 = heading_134 + ">>(ii) restore the premises to their original condition"
CONTEXT(heading_135, 'or')
heading_134 = heading_132 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'compensate the lessor for the reasonable cost incurred by the lessor to remove the thing or restore the premises.')
heading_133 = heading_131 + ">>(2) Subsection (1) applies to a prescribed modification made in accordance with section 50M only to the extent that the lessor"
heading_134 = heading_133 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'remove an attached thing')
heading_135 = heading_133 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_135, 'restore the premises to their original condition')
heading_136 = heading_133 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_136, 'compensate the lessor for removing an attached thing or restoring the premises.')
heading_134 = heading_131 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'If restoration of the premises mentioned in subsection (2) is carried out by a tradesperson, the tenant must give the lessor a copy of the invoice of the tradesperson within 14 days after the day on which the restoration is completed.')
heading_132 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50ZD inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]  50ZE. Tenant responsible for damage caused by making or removing modification or restoring premises"
heading_133 = heading_132 + ">>(1) This section applies if the tenant causes damage to residential premises when "
heading_134 = heading_133 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'making a modification to the premises or')
heading_135 = heading_133 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_135, 'if the modification included attaching a thing to the premises  removing the attached thing or')
heading_136 = heading_133 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_136, 'restoring the premises to their original condition.')
heading_134 = heading_132 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_134, 'The tenant must give the lessor a written notice that the damage has been caused to the premises.')
heading_135 = heading_132 + ">>(3) The lessor may require the tenant to "
heading_136 = heading_135 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_136, 'repair the damage and restore the premises to their original condition or')
heading_137 = heading_135 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_137, 'compensate the lessor for the reasonable cost incurred by the lessor to repair the damage and restore the premises to their original condition.')
heading_133 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 50ZE inserted No. 11 of 2024 s. 33.]; Division 3  General  [Heading inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 47.]"
heading_134 = heading_133 + ">>51. Tenant to be notified of lessors name and address"
heading_135 = heading_134 + ">>(1) Unless subsection (2) applies, at the time of entering into a residential tenancy agreement the lessor must notify the tenant, or cause the tenant to be notified, in writing of "
heading_136 = heading_135 + ">>(a) if the lessor is an individual  the full name and address of "
heading_137 = heading_136 + ">>(i) the lessor and"
heading_138 = heading_137 + ">>(ii) any person having superior title to that of the lessor"
CONTEXT(heading_138, 'or')
heading_137 = heading_135 + ">>(b) if the lessor is a body corporate  the full name and business address of the secretary of the body corporate."
CONTEXT(heading_137, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_136 = heading_134 + ">>(2) If residential premises that are the subject of a residential tenancy agreement are managed by a property manager, the lessor and the property manager must, at the time of entering into the agreement, notify the tenant, or cause the tenant to be notified, in writing of "
heading_137 = heading_136 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_137, 'the full name of the lessor and')
heading_138 = heading_136 + ">>(b) the full name and address of the property manager."
CONTEXT(heading_138, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_137 = heading_134 + ">>(3) Where a person succeeds another person as the lessor under a residential tenancy agreement, the new lessor must, within 14 days after the succession, notify the tenant, or cause the tenant to be notified, in writing of "
heading_138 = heading_137 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_138, 'the full name and address of the new lessor and')
heading_139 = heading_137 + ">>(b) where the new lessor is a body corporate, the full name and business address of the secretary of the body corporate."
CONTEXT(heading_139, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_138 = heading_134 + ">>(4) Where any name or address of which the lessor is required to notify the tenant under this section is changed, the lessor must, within 14 days after the change, notify the tenant, or cause the tenant to be notified, in writing of the changed name or address."
CONTEXT(heading_138, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_134 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 51 inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 48 amended No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_135 = heading_134 + ">>52. Failure to pay rent with intention it be recovered from security bond"
heading_136 = heading_135 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_136, 'A tenant shall not fail or refuse to pay any rent due under a residential tenancy agreement with the intention that the amount of such rent be recovered by the lessor from the security bond paid by the tenant.')
heading_137 = heading_135 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_137, 'Penalty a fine of $5 000.')
heading_135 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 52 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 55 No. 60 of 2011 s. 49, 88 and 89.]"
heading_136 = heading_135 + ">>53. Tenants name, place of employment and forwarding address"
heading_137 = heading_136 + ">>(1) A tenant under a residential tenancy agreement must not falsely state to the lessor the tenants name or place of employment."
CONTEXT(heading_137, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_138 = heading_136 + ">>(2) Where a tenant has stated a place of employment to the lessor and that place is changed, the tenant must, within 14 days after the change, notify the lessor, or cause the lessor to be notified, in writing of the new place of employment."
CONTEXT(heading_138, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_139 = heading_136 + ">>(3) A tenant under a residential tenancy agreement must, at the time of delivering up possession of the premises to which the agreement relates, notify the lessor, or cause the lessor to be notified, in writing of "
heading_140 = heading_139 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_140, 'the address at which the tenant intends to next reside or')
heading_141 = heading_139 + ">>(b) the tenants postal address."
CONTEXT(heading_141, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_136 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 53 inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 50 amended No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_137 = heading_136 + ">>54. Lessor to deliver copy of agreement to tenant"
heading_138 = heading_137 + ">>(1) A lessor or a property manager of residential premises who has required or invited a tenant to sign a written residential tenancy agreement or memorandum thereof shall "
heading_139 = heading_138 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_139, 'provide the tenant with a copy of the document at the time at which it is signed by the tenant and')
heading_140 = heading_138 + ">>(b) ensure that a fully executed copy of the document is delivered to the tenant within 14 days after it has been signed and delivered by the tenant, or, where that is not reasonably practicable in the circumstances, within such longer period as is so practicable."
CONTEXT(heading_140, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_139 = heading_137 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_139, 'If a lessor or a property manager of residential premises fails to execute and deliver a copy of the document in accordance with subsection (1)(b), acceptance of rent by the lessor or property manager without reservation shall give to the document the same effect as if it had been fully executed.')
heading_137 = heading_27 + ">>[Section 54 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 55 No. 60 of 2011 s. 51 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_138 = heading_137 + ">>55"
CONTEXT(heading_138, 'Cost of written agreement to be borne by lessor')
heading_15 = heading_13 + ">>Where a lessor requires the execution of a written residential tenancy agreement or a memorandum of a residential tenancy  [Section 55 inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 52.]"
heading_16 = heading_15 + ">>56. Discrimination against tenants with children"
heading_17 = heading_16 + ">>(1) A person shall not refuse, or cause any person to refuse, to grant a tenancy to any person on the ground that it is intended that a child should live in the premises."
CONTEXT(heading_17, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_18 = heading_16 + ">>(2) A person shall not "
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_19, 'instruct any person not to grant or')
heading_20 = heading_18 + ">>(b) state the persons intention, whether by advertisement or otherwise, not to grant,; a tenancy to any person on the ground that it is intended that a child should live in the premises."
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.; [Section 56 amended No. 59 of 1995 s. 55 No. 60 of 2011 s. 53 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>56A"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'Discrimination against tenants subjected or exposed to family violence')
heading_22 = heading_20 + ">>A person must not refuse, or cause any person to refuse, to grant a tenancy to any person on the ground that the person "
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'has been or might be subjected or exposed to family violence or')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'has been convicted of a charge relating to family violence.')
heading_23 = heading_20 + ">>Penalty a fine of $5 000."
CONTEXT(heading_23, '[Section 56A inserted No. 3 of 2019 s. 13.]')
heading_17 = heading_15 + ">>57. Accelerated rent and liquidated damages prohibited"
heading_18 = heading_17 + ">>(1) Where a residential tenancy agreement provides that, upon breach by the tenant of the agreement to pay rent or any other term of the agreement or breach of this Act or any other written law, the tenant is liable to pay "
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_19, 'all or any part of the rent remaining payable under the agreement or')
heading_20 = heading_18 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'rent of an increased amount or')
heading_21 = heading_18 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'any amount by way of a penalty or')
heading_22 = heading_18 + ">>(d) any amount by way of liquidated damages,"
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>the provision is to that extent void and of no effect.  (2A) A lessor or property manager who executes a residential tenancy agreement with a provision of the kind referred to in subsection (1) commits an offence."
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_19 = heading_17 + ">>(2) Where a residential tenancy agreement provides that, if the tenant does not breach the agreement to pay rent or any other term of the agreement or any provision of this Act or any other written law, the rent shall or may be decreased or the tenant shall or may be granted or paid a rebate, refund or other benefit, the agreement shall be deemed to have been varied from the commencement of the tenancy so that the tenant is entitled to the reduction, rebate, refund or other benefit in any event."
CONTEXT(heading_19, '[Section 57 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 54 and 88 No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]')
heading_18 = heading_15 + ">>58. Duty of mitigation"
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>The rules under the law of contract relating to mitigation of loss or damage upon breach of a contract apply to and in relation to a breach of a residential tenancy agreement."
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>[Section 58 amended No. 60 of 2011 s. 55.]"
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>59A. Minors"
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>(1) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'minor means a person who has reached 16 years of age but who has not reached 18 years of age.')
heading_23 = heading_21 + ">>(2) Despite any other law in force in this State "
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'a minor has the capacity to enter into a residential tenancy agreement as a tenant and')
heading_25 = heading_23 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'a residential tenancy agreement may be enforced in accordance with this Act against a minor who is a tenant.')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>[Section 59A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 56.]"
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>59B. Death of one of 2 or more tenants"
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>(1) This section applies if "
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_24, '2 or more tenants are parties to a residential tenancy agreement and')
heading_25 = heading_23 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'the tenants are not joint tenants under the agreement and')
heading_26 = heading_23 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'one of the tenants dies.')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>(2) On the death of the tenant "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'the deceased tenants interest in the tenancy ends and')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'the agreement continues in force with the parties to the agreement being the lessor and the surviving tenant or tenants.')
heading_25 = heading_22 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'Subsection (2) does not affect, as between the deceased tenant and the surviving tenant or tenants, any right (including, in particular, a right relating to a security bond) or liability of the deceased tenant existing immediately before the deceased tenants death.')
heading_22 = heading_19 + ">>[Section 59B inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 56.]"
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>59C. Recognition of certain persons as tenants"
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'A person who is not a tenant but who is occupying residential premises to which a residential tenancy agreement applies may apply to a competent court to be recognised as a tenant under the agreement or to be joined as a party to any proceedings before the court relating to the premises, or both.')
heading_25 = heading_23 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'An application by a person to be recognised as a tenant may be made at the same time as any other application or during proceedings before the court or independently of any such other application or proceedings.')
heading_26 = heading_23 + ">>(3) On application by a person under this section the court may make either or both of the following orders "
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'an order recognising the person as a tenant under a residential tenancy agreement and in that case the person is to be taken, for the purposes of this or any other Act and of the agreement, to be a tenant under the agreement')
heading_28 = heading_26 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'an order joining the person as a party to proceedings.')
heading_27 = heading_23 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'In making an order referred to in subsection (3)(a) the court may order that the tenancy be continued on such of the terms and conditions of the residential tenancy agreement as it thinks are appropriate having regard to the circumstances of the case.')
heading_23 = heading_19 + ">>[Section 59C inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 56.]"
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>59D. Tenant compensation bonds"
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>(1) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'tenant compensation order means an order under section 15(2)(b) in relation to a failure by a lessor to reimburse a tenant for reasonable expenses incurred by the tenant in arranging for urgent repairs to be carried out, and paying for those repairs, in accordance with section 43.')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>(2) A court that makes a tenant compensation order against a lessor may make a further order requiring the lessor to pay to the bond administrator a tenant compensation bond to cover any future tenant compensation orders that might be made against the lessor in respect of "
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'a particular tenant or particular residential premises of the lessor or')
heading_28 = heading_26 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'any tenant or residential premises of the lessor.')
heading_27 = heading_24 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'The tenant compensation bond is to be an amount determined by the court.')
heading_28 = heading_24 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'The lessor may apply to the court for an order that the whole or part of a tenant compensation bond is to be paid back to the lessor.')
heading_29 = heading_24 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'The court may make the order referred to in subsection (4) if it is satisfied that it is appropriate in the circumstances to do so.')
heading_30 = heading_24 + ">>(6) The bond administrator must pay the amount of the tenant compensation bond in accordance with "
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'Schedule 1 clause 10 or')
heading_32 = heading_30 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'an order under subsection (5) and Schedule 1 clause 11.')
heading_24 = heading_19 + ">>[Section 59D inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 56.]"
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>59E. Interference with quiet enjoyment"
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'A lessor who causes or permits interference with the reasonable peace, comfort or privacy of the tenant in the tenants use of the premises commits an offence.')
heading_20 = heading_18 + ">>Penalty for this subsection a fine of $10 000."
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'The liability of a person in civil proceedings is not affected by the commencement of proceedings against the person for an offence under subsection (1) or the conviction of the person in proceedings for the offence.')
heading_22 = heading_20 + ">>(3) When a charge of an offence under subsection (1) relates to a failure by the lessor to give the tenant a copy of a key to the premises, it is a defence to the charge to prove that "
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'the copy of the key had been given to the lessor under section 45(2)(b) and')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>(b) the tenant was a person to whom the lessor was instructed not to give the copy of the key under section 45(2)(c)(ii).; [Section 59E inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 56 amended No. 3 of 2019 s. 14 and 25.]"
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>59F. Offences relating to security of residential premises"
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'A lessor or tenant who breaches the term referred to in section 45(1)(b) without reasonable excuse commits an offence.')
heading_21 = heading_18 + ">>Penalty for this subsection a fine of $20 000."
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'A property manager of residential premises who, without reasonable excuse alters, removes or adds a lock or other means of securing the residential premises without the consent of the tenant given at, or immediately before, the time that the alteration, removal or addition is carried out, in addition to any civil liability that the property manager might incur, commits an offence.')
