heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>75. Termination of agreement for breach by lessor"
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'A competent court may, upon application by the tenant under a residential tenancy agreement, terminate the agreement, if it is satisfied that the lessor has breached the agreement and the breach is in the circumstances of the case such as to justify termination of the agreement.')
heading_34 = heading_32 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'Where a court terminates a residential tenancy agreement under this section, it shall also make an order for possession of the premises and shall specify a day as from which the orders shall operate.')
heading_32 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 75 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120 No. 60 of 2011 s. 88 and 89.]"
heading_33 = heading_32 + ">>76A. Termination of agreement by lessor if premises abandoned"
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'If a lessor suspects on reasonable grounds that a tenant has abandoned the residential premises, the lessor may give a written notice to the tenant terminating the agreement.')
heading_35 = heading_33 + ">>(2) The notice must be in the approved form and must "
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'be signed by or for the lessor or property manager and')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'identify the residential premises and')
heading_38 = heading_35 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'state the lessor is terminating the agreement because the tenant has abandoned the premises.')
heading_36 = heading_33 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'If the tenant does not take action under section 76B to dispute the notice within 7 days after being given the notice, the tenant is to be taken to have abandoned the premises.')
heading_33 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 76A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 74 amended No. 11 of 2024 s. 37.]"
heading_34 = heading_33 + ">>76B. Dispute about s. 76A notice"
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>(1) If the tenant wishes to dispute a notice given under section 76A, the tenant may apply to a competent court for an order "
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'setting aside the notice or')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'for compensation.')
heading_36 = heading_34 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'The application must be made within 28 days after the notice is given.')
heading_37 = heading_34 + ">>(3) On an application under this section, the court may "
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'if the application was made within 7 days after the notice was given  make an order setting aside the notice or')
heading_39 = heading_37 + ">>(b) if paragraph (a) does not apply  make any of the following orders "
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>(i) an order terminating the agreement"
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_41, '(ii) an order requiring the lessor to pay to the tenant the amount stated by the court as compensation for loss or expense incurred by the tenant because of the termination of the agreement')
heading_42 = heading_40 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_42, '(iii) any other order it considers appropriate.')
heading_34 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 76B inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 74.]; Division 5  General  [Heading inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 74.]"
heading_35 = heading_34 + ">>76C. Fixed term tenancies continued as periodic tenancies"
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'This section applies to a residential tenancy agreement that creates a tenancy for a fixed term unless the agreement is terminated before the expiry day.')
heading_37 = heading_35 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'Subject to subsection (3), a residential tenancy agreement continues as a periodic tenancy after the expiry day on the same terms that applied immediately before the expiry day.')
heading_38 = heading_35 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'A competent court may, upon application by the lessor or tenant, make such modification to the terms of the residential tenancy agreement as may be necessary for, or appropriate to, its continuance.')
heading_35 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 76C inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 74.]"
heading_36 = heading_35 + ">>76. Compensation to lessor for holding over"
heading_37 = heading_36 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_37, 'Where a tenant fails to comply with an order for possession made by a court under this Part, the lessor shall be entitled to compensation for any loss caused by that failure.')
heading_38 = heading_36 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_38, 'A competent court may, upon application by the lessor, order the tenant to pay to the lessor any compensation to which the lessor is entitled under this section.')
heading_36 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 76 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(1) and (3) No. 60 of 2011 s. 89.]"
heading_37 = heading_36 + ">>77. Abandonment of premises"
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>(1) If the lessor suspects on reasonable grounds that the tenant has abandoned the residential premises, the lessor may give to the tenant a written notice stating that "
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'the lessor suspects that the tenant has abandoned the premises and')
heading_40 = heading_38 + ">>(b) unless the tenant informs the lessor within 24 hours after the giving of the notice that the tenant has not abandoned the premises, the lessor "
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>(i) will enter the premises for the purpose of inspecting and securing them and"
CONTEXT(heading_41, '(ii) may give to the tenant a notice under section 76A or apply to a competent court for an order under section 78A.')
heading_39 = heading_37 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'The notice under subsection (1) must be in the approved form.')
heading_40 = heading_37 + ">>(3) The lessor must give the notice to the tenant by "
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'leaving a copy at the premises and')
heading_42 = heading_40 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'leaving a copy at the tenants last known place of employment.')
heading_41 = heading_37 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'If the tenant fails to notify the lessor within 24 hours after notice has been given under subsection (3) that the premises have not been abandoned, the lessor may enter the premises for the purposes of inspecting and securing them.')
heading_37 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 77 inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 75 amended No. 11 of 2024 s. 39.]"
heading_38 = heading_37 + ">>78A. Order about abandonment"
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_39, 'If a lessor suspects on reasonable grounds that the tenant has abandoned the residential premises, the lessor may apply to a competent court for an order under this section.')
heading_40 = heading_38 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'The lessor may make the application instead of giving a notice under section 76A to the tenant.')
heading_41 = heading_38 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'If an application is made, the court may make an order declaring that the premises were abandoned by the tenant on the day stated in the order.')
heading_42 = heading_38 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'If the court makes an order under subsection (3), the tenant is taken to have abandoned the premises on the day stated in the order.')
heading_38 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 78A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 75.]"
heading_39 = heading_38 + ">>78B. Review of abandonment order"
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_40, 'The tenant under a residential tenancy agreement who is dissatisfied with a decision of a court under section 78A(3) declaring that the tenant abandoned the premises on a stated day may apply to the court for a review of the decision.')
heading_41 = heading_39 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'The application must be made within 28 days after the decision is made.')
heading_42 = heading_39 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'The review is to be by way of a rehearing.')
heading_43 = heading_39 + ">>(4) The court "
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'must exercise its original jurisdiction for the review and')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'may make an order under this section if it is satisfied the applicant did not abandon the premises or only abandoned the premises on a day after the day stated.')
heading_44 = heading_39 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'The order the court may make is an order requiring the lessor under the agreement to pay to the tenant an amount the court considers appropriate as compensation for any loss or expense incurred by the tenant by the termination of the agreement.')
heading_39 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 78B inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 75.]"
heading_40 = heading_39 + ">>78. Right of lessor to compensation where tenant abandons premises"
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_41, 'Where a tenant under a residential tenancy agreement abandons the premises, the lessor shall be entitled to compensation from the tenant for any loss (including loss of rent) caused thereby, but shall take all reasonable steps to mitigate such loss and shall not be entitled to compensation in respect of any loss that could have been avoided thereby.')
heading_42 = heading_40 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'A competent court may, upon application by the lessor, order the tenant to pay to the lessor any compensation to which the lessor is entitled under this section.')
heading_40 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 78 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(1) No. 60 of 2011 s. 88 and 89.]"
heading_41 = heading_40 + ">>79. Abandoned goods   (1A) In this section ; goods does not include a tenants document as defined in section 80A."
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>(1) Where a residential tenancy agreement is terminated and goods are left on the premises that were subject to the agreement, the lessor may, after the expiration of 2 days from the termination of the agreement, remove and destroy or dispose of the goods if "
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'the goods are perishable foodstuffs or')
heading_44 = heading_42 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'the estimated value of the goods is less than the total estimated cost of the removal, storage and sale of the goods.')
heading_43 = heading_41 + ">>(2) Where a residential tenancy agreement is terminated and goods are left on the premises that were subject to the agreement and have not been removed for destruction or disposal under subsection (1), the lessor shall store them in a safe place and manner for a period of not less than 60 days after the day on which the agreement is terminated."
CONTEXT(heading_43, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_44 = heading_41 + ">>(3) A lessor who stores goods under subsection (2) must cause notice in or to the effect of the approved form "
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'to be given to the tenant within 7 days after the day on which the goods were stored or')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>(b) to be "
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>(i) made publicly available in any manner prescribed for the purposes of this paragraph,"
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>(ii) posted in a prominent position on the premises that were subject to the former agreement within 9 days after the day on which the goods were stored."
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_45 = heading_41 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'At the request of a lessor, the Commissioner may state in writing whether or not in the Commissioners opinion there are reasonable grounds for believing that subsection (1) applies in respect of particular goods.')
heading_46 = heading_41 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'Where a lessor has been found liable to the owner of goods in respect of the removal, destruction or disposal of the goods, being goods that were left on premises that were subject to a former agreement, and it is proved that the lessor removed and destroyed or disposed of the goods in reliance upon a statement of the Commissioner under subsection (4), the lessor shall be entitled to be paid from moneys standing to the credit of the Rental Accommodation Account, in accordance with clause 3(3)(a) of Schedule 1, an amount equal to the amount in respect of which the lessor has been found liable.')
heading_47 = heading_41 + ">>(6) Where "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'a residential tenancy agreement has been terminated and')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'goods have been left on the premises that were subject to the agreement and')
heading_50 = heading_47 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'at the request of the lessor, the Commissioner has made a statement in writing that in the Commissioners opinion there are reasonable grounds for believing that subsection (1) does not apply to the goods and')
heading_51 = heading_47 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'the total cost of removing, storing and selling the goods does in fact exceed the value of the goods,')
heading_48 = heading_41 + ">>(7)"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'A person who has a lawful right to goods removed and stored under subsection (2) may at any time before the goods are sold under subsection (8) reclaim the goods upon paying to the lessor the reasonable costs of the removal and storage of the goods.')
heading_49 = heading_41 + ">>(8)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'Where goods are stored under subsection (2) and have not been reclaimed within 60 days after the day on which they were removed and stored, the lessor shall as soon as practicable after the expiration of that period cause them to be sold by public auction.')
heading_50 = heading_41 + ">>(9) If goods are stored, removed and sold by public auction under this section, the lessor is entitled to retain out of the proceeds of the sale the reasonable costs of removing, storing and selling the goods.  (10) Where goods have been sold under this section by a lessor, the lessor may, upon application containing the prescribed information, pay into court an amount that a competent court is satisfied represents the balance of the proceeds of the sale after deduction of any amount to which the lessor is entitled under subsection (9) and any amount that the lessor is owed under the former agreement, and, where such payment is made, the receipt of the court for the moneys paid shall be sufficient discharge to the lessor of the lessors liability in respect of the moneys.  (11) Any moneys paid into court under subsection (10) shall be credited to the Rental Accommodation Account as provided by clause 3(2)(c) of Schedule 1.  (12) Where any application is made to a competent court by any person claiming any amount credited to the Rental"
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'in respect of the removal, destruction or disposal of goods under subsection (1) or')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'in respect of the removal, storage or sale under this section of goods to which subsection (1) does not apply, except liability for intentional or negligent damage to the goods or where the lessor has actual notice of any interest in the goods of any person other than the tenant and fails to take all reasonable steps to notify that person of the whereabouts of the goods and afford that person a reasonable opportunity to reclaim the goods.  (15) Where a dispute arises between a lessor and a tenant in respect of goods to which this section applies, a competent court may, upon application by such person, order the payment of any amount or make such other order as it considers appropriate in the circumstances.')
heading_41 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 79 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 14 and 18 No. 59 of 1995 s. 56 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120 and 121 No. 77 of 2006 Sch. 1 cl. 149(1) and (5) No. 60 of 2011 s. 76, 88 and 89 No. 42 of 2016 s. 5 No. 11 of 2024 s. 40.]"
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>80A. Abandoned documents"
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>(1) In this section ; tenants document means "
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'an official document or')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'a photograph or')
heading_46 = heading_43 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'correspondence or')
heading_47 = heading_43 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'any other document which it would be reasonable to expect that a person would want to keep.')
heading_44 = heading_42 + ">>(2) This section applies if "
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'a residential tenancy agreement is terminated and')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'a tenants document is left on premises the subject of the agreement.')
heading_45 = heading_42 + ">>(3) The lessor must take reasonable care of the tenants document for a period of 60 days after the termination of the agreement."
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_46 = heading_42 + ">>(4) The lessor must, during the period of 60 days after the termination of the agreement, take reasonable steps to notify the tenant "
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'that the document was left at the premises and')
heading_48 = heading_46 + ">>(b) as to when and from where the document may be collected."
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_47 = heading_42 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'A person who has a lawful right to the document may reclaim it at any time before it is disposed of in accordance with subsection (7) if the person pays the lessor the reasonable costs, if any, incurred by the lessor in discharging the duties imposed on the lessor under this section in relation to that document.')
heading_48 = heading_42 + ">>(6) If a person who has a lawful right to a document reclaims the document and pays an amount equal to the reasonable costs incurred by the lessor in discharging the duties imposed on the lessor under this section, the lessor must give the document to that person."
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'Penalty for this subsection a fine of $5 000.')
heading_49 = heading_42 + ">>(7)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'If the document has not been claimed under subsection (5) within 60 days after the day on which the agreement was')
heading_50 = heading_42 + ">>(8)"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'If a lessor destroys or otherwise disposes of a document under subsection (7), a competent court may, on an application by the lessor, make an order for the payment to the lessor out of moneys standing to the credit of the Rental Accommodation Account, in accordance with Schedule 1 clause 3(3)(a), of an amount equal to the reasonable costs incurred by the lessor in discharging the duties imposed on the lessor under this section.')
heading_51 = heading_42 + ">>(9)"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'Nothing in this section affects the operation of any other Act or law affecting the destruction or disposal of a document.')
heading_42 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 80A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 77 amended No. 3 of 2019 s. 25.]"
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>80. Recovery of possession of premises prohibited except by court order"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'No person shall except under an order of a competent court enter premises or any part of premises of which a person has possession as a tenant under a residential tenancy agreement or a former tenant holding over after termination of a residential tenancy agreement for the purpose of recovering possession of the premises or part of the premises, whether entry is effected peaceably or otherwise.')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'Penalty a fine of $20 000.')
heading_43 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 80 amended No. 50 of 1988 s. 18 No. 59 of 1995 s. 55 No. 59 of 2004 s. 120(1) No. 60 of 2011 s. 78 and 88.]"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>81A. Mortgagee repossessions of rented properties"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>(1) In this section "
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'notice to vacate, in relation to residential premises, means a written notice to vacate the premises')
heading_47 = heading_45 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'specified date means a date, specified in a notice to vacate, by which the tenant is to vacate the residential premises.')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'If a residential tenancy agreement is terminated under section 60(1)(e), the mortgagee is not to take possession of the residential premises from a tenant who is holding over after termination of the agreement unless the mortgagee, after becoming entitled to take possession, gives the tenant a notice to vacate the premises.')
heading_47 = heading_44 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'The notice to vacate must be in the approved form and must include a specified date that is not less than 30 days after the date on which the notice is given to the tenant.')
heading_48 = heading_44 + ">>(4) The tenant who is holding over after termination of the residential tenancy agreement "
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'is not, during the period of 30 days following the date on which the tenant is given the notice to vacate, required to pay any rent, fee or other charge to occupy the residential premises and')
heading_50 = heading_48 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'is, if the tenant has paid any rent in advance for any part of that period, entitled to be repaid the amount of that rent.')
heading_49 = heading_44 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'A competent court may, on application by the tenant, order the repayment to the tenant of any such amount referred to in subsection (4)(a) or (b).')
heading_50 = heading_44 + ">>(6) The mortgagee (or any person acting on behalf of the mortgagee) is, during the period in which the tenant is holding over after termination of the residential tenancy agreement, entitled to enter the residential premises to show the premises to prospective purchasers on a reasonable number of occasions, but only if the tenant "
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'is given reasonable notice of each such occasion and')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'agrees to the date and time of the inspection.')
heading_51 = heading_44 + ">>(7) This section does not prevent the mortgagee from "
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'taking possession of the residential premises before the specified date if the tenant voluntarily vacates the premises before that date or')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'changing the specified date to a later date by further notice in writing given to the tenant or')
heading_54 = heading_51 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'entering into a new residential tenancy agreement with the tenant in respect of the residential premises.')
heading_52 = heading_44 + ">>(8)"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'This section extends to a tenant who is, immediately before the commencement of this section, holding over after termination of the residential tenancy agreement.')
heading_53 = heading_44 + ">>(9)"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'This section has effect despite the terms of any court order made before the commencement of this section or any contract or other agreement.')
heading_44 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 81A inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 79 amended No. 3 of 2019 s. 19 No. 11 of 2024 s. 41.]"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>81B. Notice of proposed recovery of premises by person with superior title"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>(1) This section applies where a person (the plaintiff"
CONTEXT(heading_46, ') brings proceedings in a competent court for the recovery of possession of residential premises.')
heading_47 = heading_45 + ">>(2) The court must not make an order for possession unless it is satisfied "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>(a) that a person is not in possession of the residential premises as "
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>(i) a tenant under a residential tenancy agreement or"
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>(ii) a tenant holding over after termination of a residential tenancy agreement"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'or')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'if there is such a person in possession of the residential premises and the plaintiff is not the lessor under the residential tenancy agreement  that the person has been given written notice of the proceedings, in the approved form, not less than 30 days before the commencement of the proceedings.')
heading_48 = heading_45 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'Failure to comply with this section does not invalidate or otherwise affect the judgment or order.')
heading_45 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 81B inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 79 amended No. 11 of 2024 s. 42.]"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>81. Order for tenancy against person with superior title"
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>(1) This section applies to a person who is or was in possession of residential premises as "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'a tenant under a residential tenancy agreement or')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>(b) a tenant holding over after termination of a residential tenancy agreement,"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'at a time when proceedings for the recovery of possession of the premises had been commenced before a court by a person (the plaintiff ) who is not the lessor under the agreement.')
heading_48 = heading_46 + ">>(2) A person to whom this section applies may apply for an order under this section and such an application may be made to "
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'the court before which the proceedings are pending or')
heading_50 = heading_48 + ">>(b) if the proceedings have been completed or possession has been recovered  a competent court,"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'within a reasonable time after the applicant was given notice of the proceedings or, if no notice was given, within a reasonable time after the recovery of possession of the residential premises.')
heading_49 = heading_46 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'The court may, on such an application, and if it thinks it appropriate to do so in the special circumstances of the case, make an order vesting a tenancy over the residential premises in the applicant.')
heading_50 = heading_46 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'The tenancy is to be held of the plaintiff, and on such terms and conditions as the court thinks fit, having regard to the circumstances of the case.')
heading_51 = heading_46 + ">>(5) Such an application or order may be made, even though "
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'notice was not given to the applicant of the proceedings brought by the plaintiff or')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'the proceedings brought by the plaintiff have been completed or possession of the residential premises has been recovered by the plaintiff.')
heading_46 = heading_24 + ">>[Section 81 inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 79.]; Part VIA  Residential tenancy databases  [Heading inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 96.]; Division 1  Preliminary  [Heading inserted No. 60 of 2011 s. 96.]"
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>82A. Terms used; In this Part "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'agent, of a lessor, means a person employed, or otherwise authorised, by the lessor to act as the lessors agent')
heading_49 = heading_47 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'database means a system, device or other thing used for storing information, whether electronically or in some other form')
heading_50 = heading_47 + ">>content3"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'database operator means an entity that operates a residential tenancy database')
heading_51 = heading_47 + ">>inaccurate, in relation to personal information in a residential tenancy database, includes information that is inaccurate because "
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'the information indicates that the person owes a lessor an amount that is more than the security bond for a residential tenancy agreement and')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'the amount owed was paid to the lessor more than 3 months after the amount became due')
heading_52 = heading_47 + ">>list, personal information about a person in a residential tenancy database "
heading_53 = heading_52 + ">>(a) means "
heading_54 = heading_53 + ">>(i) to enter the personal information into the database or"
heading_55 = heading_54 + ">>(ii) to give the personal information to a database operator or someone else for entry into the database"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'and')
heading_54 = heading_52 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'includes to amend personal information about a person in the database to include additional personal information about the person')
heading_53 = heading_47 + ">>out-of-date, in relation to personal information in a residential tenancy database, means the information is no longer accurate because "
heading_54 = heading_53 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'for a listing made on the basis the person owes a lessor an amount that is more than the security bond for a residential tenancy agreement  the amount owed was paid to the lessor within 3 months after the amount became due or')
heading_55 = heading_53 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'for a listing made on the basis a court has made an order terminating the residential tenancy agreement  the order has been set aside on appeal')
heading_54 = heading_47 + ">>content7"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'residential premises includes a long-stay site in a residential park as those terms are defined in the  Residential Parks (Long-stay Tenants) Act 2006')
heading_55 = heading_47 + ">>content8"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'residential tenancy agreement includes a long-stay agreement as defined in the  Residential Parks (Long-stay Tenants) Act 2006')
heading_56 = heading_47 + ">>residential tenancy database means a database "
heading_57 = heading_56 + ">>(a) containing personal information "
heading_58 = heading_57 + ">>(i) relating to, or arising from, the occupation of residential premises under a residential tenancy agreement or"
